title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix boiling water and jello, stir well.
Stir in pineapple and pie filling.
Pour into mold or 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Refrigerate until jelled.
Beat cream cheese until smooth, add sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Cover top of gelatin.
Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: easy cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add 1/2 cup shortening and 2/3 cup milk.
Mix at medium speed until everything is mixed and then add 2/3 cup milk. Add eggs and vanilla and mix for 3 minutes.
Pour into two greased and floured 9-inch round baking pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix salmon, Cheddar cheese soup, bread crumbs, eggs, onion and lemon juice.
Place into a greased loaf pan and bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans together and pat out in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: In medium mixing bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together egg whites, banana, sugar and oil.
Stir flour mixture into banana mixture just until moistened.

title: white cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, then add sifted flour and baking powder.
Add egg whites (well beaten) and vanilla.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: helen's toffee squares
directions: In mixing bowl, cream together butter and brown sugar until light colored and fluffy.
Add egg yolk and vanilla; gradually beat in flour until smooth and blended.
(Dough will be thick.) Spread evenly on ungreased 16 x 14 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until crust is golden brown and puffy. Remove from oven.

title: dirty worms
directions: Melt both package of chips together.
Add chow mein noodles. Spoon onto waxed paper and let cook until hard.

title: creamy fruit dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine cream cheese, marshmallow cream and fruit juice.
Blend with electric mixer until smooth.
Ready to serve.
Keep refrigerated.
Dip any fruit or melon in cream.

title: stacked enchiladas
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a large skillet.
Add chili powder, salt, cumin and oregano.
Cook for 1 minute.
In a blender, mix at low speed the flour, chicken broth and about 1 cup water.
Pour into skillet.
You might have to add more water to make sauce thin.
Add garlic.
Simmer 1/2 to 1 hour, until it thickens.

title: homemade sausage
directions: Mix ingredients and roll in foil, shiny side next to meat. Wrap and store in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Punch hole in bottom of package. Cook in oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Chill and slice.

title: caramel corn
directions: Have popped corn ready.
In a saucepan, measure brown sugar, margarine and Karo syrup.
Bring to boil; boil 5 minutes.
Then add salt and baking soda.
Stir well.
Pour over popped corn; stir until coated.
Spread in large, shallow baking pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 250°.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Combine water, yeast and a little sugar until foamy.
Add oil and sugar.
Gradually add flour, mixing and kneading until mixture doesn't stick to your hands or until smooth.
Set aside to raise; double in size.
Separate dough into 3 equal loaves.
Roll out like cinnamon rolls.
Brush with beaten eggs.
Top with pepperoni, onions and cheese.
Roll up and seal ends good.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove immediately from pans and brush with butter.
Slice and microwave for a few seconds with butter.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: chewy chocolate macaroons
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Stir coconut and cocoa together.
Stir in milk and vanilla until blended.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on sheet.
Press cherry half into center of each cookie.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool at room temperature.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy; blend in cheese, butter, flour, green onions
and
broccoli.
Pour
into
greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish; top with croutons.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: seven-up party salad
directions: Combine 7-Up and marshmallows in saucepan.
Cook until melted. Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Cream the cheese in mixing bowl.
Add hot mixture to cheese and beat until smooth.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Chill until almost set.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix sugar, flour, milk, egg, salt and pepper until smooth; add vinegar and water.
Put in saucepan, heat until thickens.
Pour over chopped cabbage.

title: dutch beans
directions: Drain beans and save juice.
Cook bacon in Dutch oven and leave grease.
Saute onion in bacon drippings.
Add sugar, vinegar and mustard.
Cook on low heat for 2 hours.
Crumble bacon; top when ready to serve.

title: pea salad
directions: Cook
frozen peas as directed.
Don't overcook.
Blanch in cool
water
and drain well.
Add the above ingredients and mix with mayonnaise.

title: thelma o'berry's spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onions, peppers and bacon.
Add sausage and hamburger. Brown meats.
Add rest of ingredients and cook for about 1 hour. Add garlic salt or powder to taste or fresh.
Salt to taste.

title: dee's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Stir together cooked macaroni, soup, cheese and water (slowly add enough water to keep moist).
Heat slowly on low heat until cheese is melted and macaroni is hot.
Serve.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand for at least 4 hours.

title: yummy oyster crackers
directions: Mix to coat crackers.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes or less. Stir after 10 minutes. Cool. Store in airtight container.

title: choco-marshmallow cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, salt, soda, sugar and cocoa. Add the remaining ingredients. Beat well. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake 8 minutes at 350° (don't overbake).

title: cheese rice
directions: Saute onion and rice in oil in large saucepan.
Add cheese, beef broth, jalapenos and butter.
Cook approximately 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix until foamy and pour on buttered table.

title: sherbet delight
directions: Mix milk and vanilla with Dream Whip; whip as directed on package.
Fold in sugar.
Add crushed macaroons and nuts to Dream Whip.
Place 1/2 of mixture in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread sherbet evenly over mixture.
Spread remaining cookie mixture over sherbet.
Freeze several hours or overnight.
Cut in squares.
Serves 12 or more.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Spread nuts and coconut in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour over coconut.
Cream sugar, cheese and butter.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie(for 1 pie)
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in sugar, eggs, Karo syrup, vanilla, chopped pecans and chocolate chips.
Pour in pie shell.
Put whole pecans in pie mix, then bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken with grapes
directions: Heat up red wine vinegar, tarragon and a little salt and pepper over high heat.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Place chicken in bowl and pour red wine vinegar over it.
Mix well; cover and put in fridge until cooled.
Add all ingredients together and mix well.

title: sour cream and dill potato salad
directions: Mix together ingredients and chill.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: corn, zucchini and tomato chowder
directions: Heat olive oil until hot in large, heavy, deep-sided pan set over medium-high heat. Add onions and cook, stirring just until softened slightly, about 3 minutes. Add corn kernels and cook and stir another 3 minutes. Add stock, salt and pepper. Bring mixture to simmer and cook, uncovered, until corn is tender, 15 to 18 minutes. Add zucchini and cook until tender, about 6 minutes. Add tomatoes and cook 3 to 4 minutes. Remove soup from heat and set aside a few minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: In a skillet over medium-high heat, brown steak in oil; drain.
Add garlic; saute for 3 minutes.
Add broth; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 12 to 16 minutes or until broth is reduced by half.
Add pepper and onion.
Combine cornstarch and water until smooth; stir into broth.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Serve over rice.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: easiest fruit dip ever!
directions: Punch down Marshmallow Fluff (in its own jar) with a spoon or fork.
Add 1 tablespoon sour cream or enough to achieve a smooth texture and stir, stir, stir!
Serve with your choice of fruit like melon balls, kiwi, strawberries or bananas; anything you like.

title: salsa grillers
directions: Split grillers lengthwise.
Be careful not to cut bottom skin. Combine nacho cheese, crushed chips and salsa in small bowl. Fill grillers with cheese mixture.
Grill until favorite doneness. Serve on your favorite hot dog roll.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Do not use mixer.
Mix by hand all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet sour mustard
directions: Let mustard and vinegar set overnight.
Cook eggs and sugar in double boiler.
Combine with mustard and vinegar.
Boil until like thin custard, about 10 minutes.
Pour into small jars.
Makes a good small gift.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, milk and egg yolks (slightly beaten) in a microwave bowl.
Cook for 10 minutes on high, stirring every 2 to 3 minutes until thickens.
Add oleo and vanilla. Stir until oleo is melted.
Add coconut.
Pour mixture into pie shells.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks.
Adding 1/4 c. sugar and 1 tsp. white vanilla or butter flavoring.
Spread on pies.
Sprinkle coconut on meringue.
Cook until lightly brown in 400° oven.

title: "french fries" casserole
directions: Saute green pepper and celery in 1/2 cup oleo.

Mix 1/4 cup oleo, flour, salt, pepper and 4 cups milk (makes white sauce). Add pimentos and shredded carrots to green pepper and celery. Layer the frozen fries on bottom of dish, alternating with sauteed vegetables.
Mix shredded cheese into white sauce; pour over vegetables.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: crab imperial
directions: Press out crab meat to remove bits of shell.
Simmer vegetables in butter.
Combine other ingredients except buttered bread crumbs. Mix gently and fill clean crab shell.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 450° for about 20 minutes or until brown.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: hamdogs
directions: Combine ham, seasonings and mayonnaise.
Slit franks almost to ends, three-quarters way through.
Stuff franks with mixture and wrap with bacon strips, securing with toothpicks.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: picnic chocolate squares
directions: Combine water, oleo and chocolate in pan; bring to boil. Remove from heat.
Add flour and sugar; mix well.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add sour cream, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: frosty ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Place in ice cream freezer; freeze according to manufacturer's directions.

title: pasta salad
directions: For dressing, stir together Italian dressing, mustard, vinegar, pepper, garlic, lemon juice and basil.
Drain cooked pasta.
Put in a large bowl.
Add vegetables and dressing; toss to mix.
Add tomatoes before serving.
For a main dish, add turkey or chicken (1 1/2 cups cooked and diced).

title: orange bread
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt (1/4 teaspoon) and sift.
Add rind to creamed mixture.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk (I use only 3/4 of a cup) to cream mixture.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 325° for one hour.

title: banana walnut bread
directions: Preheat oven
to 350°.	In a small bowl, smash bananas. Stir in	baking	soda.
In
a
large bowl, cream margarine and sugar together.
Mix
in	eggs.
Stir
in flour and banana and soda mixture.
Stir in walnuts.	Pour into loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: hamburger-macaroni casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain fat.
Cook elbows to "al dente"; drain and combine with hamburger.
Mix together tomatoes, salt, pepper and cheese.
Combine this with hamburger and macaroni.

title: caramel dumplings
directions: Let boil for a few minutes.

title: hamburger hot pot
directions: In skillet, lightly brown ground beef; drain.
Add garlic powder, salt and pepper, set aside.
Place half the potatoes and half the onion in greased crock pot.
Add browned ground beef. Top with remaining potatoes and onions.
Combine mushroom soup and water; spread over top.
Cover and cook on low for 8-10 hours, or high for 3-4 hours.

title: j.b.'s hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add hot water and margarine. Stir until hot and bubbly.

title: wilt dressing
directions: Combine and cook over stove until slightly thickened.
Store in jar in refrigerator.
Serve over leaf lettuce or can be used for slaw or potato salad.

title: chili with corn dumplings
directions: In a large skillet, heat chili and water to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Prepare muffin mix as directed on package, but decrease milk to 1/2 cup and stir in cheese.
Drop by spoonfuls onto boiling chili. Cook, uncovered, over low heat for 10 minutes. Cover and cook 10 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Crush crackers; add sugar and melted butter.
Mix well.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare whip per package instructions. Soften cheese.
Add sugar and blend.
Add Dream Whip and beat until fluffy.

title: brownies
directions: Mix flour and sugar; set aside.
Mix and bring to boil margarine, cocoa and water.
Add sugar and flour mixture.
In bowl mix eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add all mixture and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mom's easy pie crust
directions: Whip shortening and boiling water with fork to "whipped cream" consistency.
Add salt to flour.

title: pineapple cream cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on package.
While cake is baking, mix together pineapple, pudding mix and Cool Whip.
Place in refrigerator to chill.
Cool cake and spread pineapple cream on top of cake.
Enjoy!

title: pink layer party cake
directions: Beat sugar and margarine together.
Mix flour and blancmange powder together.
Add egg and flour alternately to mixture.
Beat well; bake in 2 greased sandwich tins for 20 minutes.
When cold, spread with layer of jam.
To ice, boil together 2 tablespoons each sugar and water and small piece of margarine.
Allow to cool; beat in sufficient pink blancmange powder to make icing of right colour and consistency.
(GE)

title: don's brownies
directions: Melt oleo. Add sugar and beat. Add cocoa and stir. Add eggs, one at a time. Beat after each egg. Add vanilla and flour. Pour into 9 x 13 cake pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Can frost if you wish.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix together.
Bake in greased casserole at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: grapefruit frosting
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients
in top of a double boiler. Beat at low speed of an
electric mixer for 30 seconds or just until mixed.
Place over
boiling
water.
Beat
constantly at high speed for 7 minutes
or
until
stiff peaks form.
Remove from heat.
Add grapefruit rind
and
vanilla.
Beat
to
2 minutes or
until
frosting is thick enough to spread.
Makes 3 3/4 cups or enough for 1 (2 layer) cake.

title: chicken in a biscuit
directions: Combine cream cheese and milk; beat until smooth.
Add chicken, pimiento, onion, salt and pepper; stir well.

title: guadalupe chili pie
directions: Brown beef and	onions in butter in 12-inch Dutch oven. Add beans, chili
powder,
salt and tomato sauce.
Cook for 15 minutes covered.
Mix
cornbread as directed and add to top of meat mixture.
Cook
for
25 minutes, until cornbread is done, at medium heat (350° to 375°).

title: tomato chutney
directions: Skin tomatoes and onions.
Seed peppers.
Pee land core apples.
Wash raisins.
Run through food chopper.
Combine all ingredients and cook until thick.
Pour into hot jars; seal at once.

title: salted nut chews
directions: Mix all ingredients, except marshmallows.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle marshmallows over hot crust; put in oven approximately 1 minute until marshmallows just begin to puff. Cool slightly.

title: zucchini loaves
directions: Mix eggs, oil and sugar; add flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add zucchini, pineapple, nuts and raisins.
Pour into lightly greased or sprayed loaf pans.
Makes 2 large loaves or several small loaves.

title: chicken biriani
directions: Fry onions and potatoes in 2 tablespoons oil until brown; set aside.
Melt butter and add chicken and tomatoes; lightly fry. Add all ingredients and 2 cups water.
Cook 40 to 45 minutes, until tender.
Serve over rice with mango chutney.

title: delicious pot roast
directions: Cook bacon in iron Dutch oven until crisp. Remove bacon and crumble. Drain off all but 2 tablespoons bacon drippings. Sprinkle both sides of roast with lemon-pepper. Brown meat on both sides.

title: cajun-scalloped sweet potatoes
directions: Adjust rack to middle of oven.
Heat oven to 425°.
Coat the bottom of a 1 1/2 to 2-quart glass baking dish with olive oil. Spray one side of a large sheet of aluminum foil with nonstick spray.
Peel the sweet potatoes and cut into paper-thin slices. Spread them in layers in prepared pan.

title: indian chickpeas
directions: Heat oil.
Add cumin and onions.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add garlic and ginger.
Cook 5 minutes on low heat.
Add turmeric, coriander, cayenne and salt.
Stir; add chopped tomatoes and garam masala. Cook on low heat 10 minutes.
Add chickpeas and lemon juice.
Cook 5 minutes; add potatoes.
Serve over white steamed basmati rice, garnished with chopped green jalapeno peppers.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Drain tuna, set aside 3/4 cup of the croutons.
Blend all ingredients and toss all together.
Transfer to a well greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with remaining 3/4 cup croutons. Place in a preheated oven at 350° for 40 minutes.
Recipe may be cut in half.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes when cut in half.

title: mexican cheese ball
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until smooth.
Shape into rolls. Sprinkle a mixture of half paprika and half chili powder over the bottom of a plastic sheet.
Drop rolls into 1 or 2 balls and roll up into balls or a ball.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine well and add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add jam and sour cream to which the soda has been added, then flour and spices, mixed.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Makes a large cake.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt one stick of butter, add crumbs and mix well.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Soften the other stick of margarine and the cream cheese to room temperature.
Mix with powdered sugar and vanilla; beat with mixer for 7 minutes.
Put on top of crumbs. Put 2 cups drained pineapple on top of this, then slice the bananas on top of pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip.
Pecans and cherries may be placed on top.

title: german chocolate cake with cocoa
directions: Cream the butter, shortening and sugar together. Add eggs, one at a time. Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add to the creamed mixture alternately with the buttermilk, half at a time.
Add coffee and vanilla. Bake in 9-inch layers for 35 minutes in a 350° preheated oven.

title: chicken-cabbage salad
directions: *She improvises on the amount of chicken and cabbage, based on how much she wants to make.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Melt marshmallows with 2 Tbsp. of strawberry juice in a double broiler, remove from heat.
Mix in strawberries, chill for 2 hours.
Fold in whipped cream and place mixture in pie shell. Refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: In casserole, put a layer of Tater Tots and a layer of beef. Save some Tater Tots for the top.
Mix soups and cheese; pour over Tater Tots and beef.
Top with reserved Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: melissa's cajun pie
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugars and flour.
Pour in butter and mix well.
Blend in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about one hour.
Reduce heat and let brown.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Prepare a greased baking dish.
Mix corn and crushed crackers. Add slightly beaten eggs and salt and pepper.
Blend in milk. Pour into prepared dish.
Top with butter.
Bake at 375° to 400° for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: diabetic no sugar cookies
directions: Combine.
Stir with a wooden spoon until well mixed.
Drop dough by tablespoons, 2 inches apart, onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: drop dumplings
directions: Note:
Omit baking powder and salt if using self-rising flour.

title: no bake orange pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in hot orange juice.
Cool until thickened slightly.
Whip evaporated milk that has been chilled; then add lemon juice.
Fold whipped evaporated milk into Jell-O mixture.
Put into crust; chill for several hours.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Mix ground beef, rice, onion, egg, salt and pepper.
Remove stem ends of green peppers and fill with beef mixture.
Shape remaining beef into small balls.
Place green peppers and meatballs in saucepan.
Add tomato puree and can of water.
Simmer for about 1 hour or until beef is done, adding water if needed.

title: cantonese carrots and green peppers
directions: In a small cup, mix sugar, vinegar and 3/4 cup broth.
In another small cup, mix the cornstarch with remaining 1/2 cup broth. Set both cups aside.
Heat oil in wok or large skillet over medium heat.
Add garlic and hot pepper.
Stir until garlic is tender. Add carrots and green peppers, stir-fry 2 minutes.
Reduce heat and add sugar-vinegar, cover and steam for 5 minutes.
Remove cover, stir in broth-cornstarch mixture.
Stir until sauce thickens.
One or 2 chili peppers leaves this dish still quite mild; four makes it hot and spicy.

title: cottage cheese jello
directions: Mix package of dry jello with all other ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except Jiffy mix.
Add it last.
Bake 15 to 25 minutes in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan in a 400° oven. When completely cool, cut into squares.

title: sarah's crab dip
directions: Combine sour cream, mayo, cream cheese and seasonings.
Mix well.
Then stir in Cheddar cheese and crab.
Cover and chill 2 hours.

title: saturday special
directions: Microwave Directions:
Crumble ground beef into 2-quart casserole.
Add onion.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes, stirring once halfway through cooking time.
Drain and return to casserole dish.
Add sour cream, soup, corn, pimiento, salt and pepper. Cover and microwave 5 minutes on High.
Top with tomato slices. Microwave for 3 minutes on High or until tomatoes are slightly softened.
Garnish with French fried onions.
Let stand 3 minutes, uncovered.
(If tomato is not used, cook an additional 3 minutes on High before adding French fried onions.)
Makes 6 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a rectangular glass dish.
Tear bread and spread over bottom.
Brown and drain sausage.
Spread over bread.
Pour cheese over sausage.
Mix eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour over cheese. Refrigerate overnight.
Uncover and bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: fake red raspberry jam
directions: Heat beet juice, Sure-Jell and lemon juice.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Add sugar and Jell-O all at once.
Bring to boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Skim foam off the top when cool.
Pour into jars and seal.
Makes 6 pint jars.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and dry mushroom caps.
Dip in melted butter in which garlic has been sauteed.
Line a buttered flat casserole with the mushrooms.
Add the mayonnaise, cheese, seasonings to the cooked and drained chopped spinach.
Fill the caps and bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: Beat eggs, m.s.g. and salt together.
Heat wok until hot; add oil and make thin pancakes out of mixture.
Pour egg by tablespoons to fry and make small pancakes.
Cut egg pancakes into thin strips. Heat wok hot and dry.
Add oil.
Sprinkle wok with salt.
Brown onion, then add rice.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients except eggs and soy sauce.
Fry and stir constantly until thoroughly mixed.
Add soy sauce and stir.
Mix in shredded eggs and serve while hot.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind the cranberries, apple and orange peel.
Mix together the orange juice, cranberries, apples and orange peel with the sugar, lemon gelatin and lemon juice.
Add boiling water.
When cool, place in refrigerator to set.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine; add soup, milk, water and cheese; beat until cheese is melted.
Add broccoli and rice; mix.
Pour in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: stove-top casserole
directions: Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper.
Brown in oil in skillet. Remove chops; drain excess fat.
Add water, sugar, 1 teaspoon salt and Hunt's to skillet.
Bring to boil.
Stir in rice.

title: beef and onion dip
directions: Blend ingredients and add diced beef.
Let set overnight. Serve with crackers.

title: quick quesadilla
directions: Lightly brush each tortilla with melted butter.
Spread cheese dip over 1 tortilla to within 1/2 inch of edges.
Sprinkle with bacon and chilies.
Top with second tortilla.
Place stacked tortillas on microwave-safe plate.
Microwave on High (100%) power for 1 1/2 minutes.
Cut into wedges.
Serve with Old El Paso Thick 'n Chunky salsa or picante, if desired.
Makes 1 quesadilla.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Blend shortening with dry ingredients.
Add milk and mix well. Turn onto floured surface and knead about 1 minute.
Divide dough into 2 parts.
Roll about 1/4-inch thick.
Spread each half with 1/2 pound sausage, which has been softened to room temperature. Put rolls into refrigerator for at least 1 hour or overnight. Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Bake in 400° oven for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 60 to 70.

title: candy strawberries
directions: Combine dry gelatin, pecans and coconut.
Stir in milk and vanilla; mix well.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape into strawberries.
Roll in red sugar.
If desired, tint sliced almonds with green food coloring and insert in top of berries to form leaves.

title: ham baked
directions: Wrap ham in heavy foil and place in deep pan.
Prior to closing foil, cover with mixture of Coke, sugar and mustard.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: brandied shrimp provencale
directions: Brown butter in saute pan lightly; add onion, garlic, and shrimp and stir with fork rapidly for 2 minutes.
Pour in brandy and light.
Shake pan fast.
Add tomatoes and parsley.
Season to taste and serve.
Yields 8 servings.

title: savory cheese soup
directions: In a large saucepan, saute onion in butter until tender. Add flour, salt, pepper and garlic powder; stir until smooth. Gradually add milk; cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Meanwhile, bring chicken broth to a boil in a small saucepan.
Add carrots and celery; simmer for 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add to milk mixture and stir until blended.
Add cheeses.
Cook and stir until melted (do not boil). Garnish with chives if desired.
Yield: about 4 servings.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix cake mix, yeast and flour together thoroughly.
Add water gradually.
Cover and let rise for 1 hour. Punch down and let rise again until double in bulk.
Divide into quarters.
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness on a floured board, brush with olive oil. Sprinkle with cinnamon, sugar and nuts.
Roll like a jelly roll and slice into 1/2-inch roll.
Place on greased (or use Pam) pan and let rise.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water.
While they cook, cook onion in 1 stick of butter and fry until transparent.
Stir in flour and salt in onions and butter.
Add milk, curry powder and bring to a boil.
Add cooked potatoes and potato water.
Simmer on low.

title: frozen rocky road squares
directions: Combine four, margarine and pecans.
Press onto bottom of 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: western hash
directions: Brown meat, then drain.
Add tomatoes, rice, green pepper, onion and seasonings.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes. Top with cheese and heat until melted.

title: whiskey cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; beat until smooth and fold in nuts and coconut if desired.
Pour into ungreased tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Five minutes before cake is done, melt 1 stick butter with 1/2 cup sugar.
Heat well, do not boil. Add 1/2 cup whiskey.
Mix well.
Remove cake from oven.
Make holes in cake.
Pour butter mixture slowly over cake to fill holes.
Leave cake in pan and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: butterscotch pudding
directions: In saucepan blend sugar, cornstarch and salt; add milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Stir small amount of hot mixture into beaten egg or yolks.
Return to hot mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Pour into pudding dishes and chill.
Makes 4 servings.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt until very fine crumbs. In jar, add egg, vinegar and ice water.
With lid on jar, shake until very well blended.
Add to flour mixture and stir until blended.
Roll into size to fit pan.

title: cheese balls
directions: Combine cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce, Accent and green onions. Add 3/4 chopped beef. Make ball. Roll in last of dried beef. Refrigerate.

title: sausage balls
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
Pinch sausage and mix with flour.
Make into small balls.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Toothpicks are optional.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° until done when tested.

title: biscuits
directions: Using the basic bread dough, pinch off biscuit size pieces of dough and flatten slightly in hand.
Put one-inch piece of medium sharp Cheddar cheese in the center and pull the edges up to seal well.
Place the sealed edge down in a lightly floured biscuit pan.
Bake at 450° for about 12 minutes.
Serve hot.
Cheese will be melted inside.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Spread the crushed pineapple, with liquid, into a greased 10 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle the dry cake mix over the pineapple. Scatter the pecans over the cake mix.
Top with pieces of butter. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: orange slice fruitcake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Set aside. Roll dates and oranges in 1/2 cup flour.
Set aside.
Mix soda and buttermilk and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in remaining flour and salt.
Fold in date mixture, coconut and nuts.
Pour into *4 small loaf pans.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours.

title: vegetable party salad
directions: Mix all together and chill about 2 hours before serving.
This makes a very colorful dish.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix oleo, sugar and flour.
Beat eggs well.
Pour into sugar and butter mixture.
Add milk and vanilla.
Beat all together. Pour into an unbaked pie shell 9-inches wide.
Bake until done at 325° to 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and roll in chopped pecans.

title: chocolate creme de menthe pie
directions: Combine milk and marshmallows in double boiler; cook until dissolved.
Cool thoroughly.
Add creme de menthe.
Combine crushed cookies and butter.
Mix well, then press in an 8-inch pie pan.
Fold the whipped cream into marshmallow mixture.
Pour in shell and sprinkle with cookie crumbs.
Chill at least 5 hours before serving.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix together eggs and sugar.
Add buttermilk and butter.
Stir well.
Add coconut and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shells. Cook at 350° in preheated oven for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 2 pies.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Blend 3 ounces cream cheese and 2 sticks butter.
Add rest of ingredients.
Separate 1 package crescent rolls.
(Use 2 triangles for each serving.)	Spoon 1/2 cup chicken mixture on one side and seal together.
Brush top with butter.
Dip in crushed seasoned croutons.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: king ranch chicken casserole
directions: Combine broth, soups and tomatoes, set aside.
In large oiled casserole layer half of tortillas, half of chicken, half of onion and one third of cheese.
Pour one-half of liquid over layers. Repeat layers of tortillas, chicken and onion; then pour remaining liquid mixture over.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Better when reheated.

title: jalapeno corn quiche
directions: *Chopped ham can be substituted for bacon.
It is still good with no meat.

title: french onion stew
directions: Place all ingredients in clay oven stew pot.
Bake at 300°F for 3 hours, stirring only 3 times.
This can also be cooked in a slow cooker for the day.

title: end of world cherry cake
directions: Spread pie filling in 8-inch ungreased square pan.
Spread dry cake mix over pie filling.
Pour butter over top of mix.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 375° until top crusts over and is golden brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter in bottom of pan.
Spread bread crumbs, enough to cover bottom of pan.
Spread chicken over crumbs, then pour mushroom and chicken soups over that.
Finish covering with bread crumbs on top.
Use broth chicken was cooked in and pour over it. Put in oven and bake until browned as desired.

title: no peek stew
directions: Mix all together, cover tight.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours. Don't peek.

title: potatoes for a crowd
directions: Mix together.
Sprinkle with crushed corn flake crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered, in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Shell and clean shrimp.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Saute shrimp, onion and garlic for 5 to 8 minutes, turning shrimp once. Transfer to hot platter or serving shells.
Add salt, pepper and lemon juice to butter in skillet and heat.
Pour over shrimp and sprinkle with parsley.
Wonderful!

title: "the world's best cookie"
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugars, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add egg; beat well.
Add oil and vanilla, mixing well.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats and remaining ingredients.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets; flatten each ball with tines of a fork.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Remove from cookie sheets; cool.
Yields 10 dozen.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Make your own spaghetti sauce that you like and set aside. Boil spaghetti noodles; drain.
Mix eggs, Parmesan cheese and melted margarine in a bowl and add to spaghetti noodles.
Mix completely.
Grease a baking dish.
Pour spaghetti noodles in baking dish and press gently to form like a crust in dish.
Pour spaghetti sauce over noodles (do not stir).
Poke holes down through spaghetti noodles to allow some of the sauce to seep through.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for about 25 minutes. Add Cheddar cheese and Parmesan cheese on top.
Return to oven for 5 more minutes to melt cheese.
Allow to cool about 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: holiday punch
directions: Combine gelatin, water and sugar; bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Add Kool-Aid, pineapple, punch and strawberries.
Freeze until later.
Remove from freezer 1 hour before serving time. When ready to serve, chop until mixture becomes slushy.
Place in punch bowl.
Add Sprite or 7-Up.

title: prune cake
directions: Blend sugar and oil; add eggs and dry ingredients with milk. Add vanilla, nuts and prunes.
Pour into square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove mushroom stems and chop finely.
Saute chopped mushrooms and onions lightly in skillet in a small amount of oil. Add bread cubes, garlic salt and lemon juice, tossing to mix. Stir in egg and simmer for 1 minute.
Stuff mushroom caps with mixture.
Arrange in oiled baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or microwave for 4 minutes.

title: crawfish jambalaya
directions: Place all ingredients in rice cooker. Stir gently until done. Serves 8.

title: too good artichoke dip
directions: Combine and mix together well all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with favorite crackers.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Use Pyrex casserole.
Grease bottom of casserole.
Layer tomatoes, croutons, onion and cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: corn with brussels sprouts
directions: Wash and prepare Brussels sprouts for cooking.
Drain liquid from corn; add enough water to make 1/2 cup liquid.
Cook Brussels sprouts in liquid for about 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; heat thoroughly.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, seasoning as desired with salt and pepper. Drain. Saute the onion in the butter.

title: pecan coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine, eggs and sugar.
Add flour, salt, baking powder, vanilla and sour cream.
Mix pecans, cinnamon and brown sugar.
Add 1/2 to cake mix.
Crumble 1/2 on top for topping. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar in a mixing bowl until light and fluffy. Add egg yolks; beat well. Mix flour and baking soda together. Add to batter mixture alternately with buttermilk and 1 tsp. vanilla, beating well after each addition. Stir in coconut and 1 cup chopped walnuts. Fold in egg whites. Pour into 3 greased and floured 9 inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until layers test done. Cool in pans for several minutes, remove to wire racks to cool completely.

title: 7-cup salad
directions: Beat sour cream and cream cheese together. Mix other ingredients in by hand.

title: seafood fettucine alfredo
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove tails and set aside.
Cook dry fettucine al dente, according to the box directions.
Rinse and drain.
Set aside.
Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in a 12-inch pan.
Add 1/8 teaspoon chopped garlic and saute for 2 minutes.
Add scallops to pan.
Saute for several minutes at medium heat, turning and stirring mixture until scallops are opaque.
Add one tablespoon of bisque and heavy cream to mixture. Increase heat to medium high until mixture boils.
Reduce heat, letting mixture simmer and thicken.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Continue to stir mixture.
Add four tablespoons of grated Romano cheese and stir.
Alfredo sauce will continue to thicken.
Add shrimp, crabmeat and fettucine to sauce.
Mix thoroughly until heated throughout.
Divide directly onto two large plates. Sprinkle with Romano cheese and chopped parsley.
Serve immediately.

title: apple ambrosia
directions: Mix all together and chill several hours or overnight before serving.

title: turkey scallop(good for leftover turkey)
directions: Prepare stuffing according to package directions for dry stuffing.
Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; top with a layer of turkey.
In a large saucepan, melt butter; blend in flour and seasonings.
Add cool broth; cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Stir small amount hot mixture into eggs; return to hot mixture.
Pour over turkey.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted halfway to center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes to set.
Serve with Pimiento Mushroom Sauce.

title: egg and asparagus casserole
directions: Drain liquid from asparagus into measuring cup.
Add enough milk to make 1 1/2 cups.
Melt butter; stir in flour, salt and cheese.
Arrange in greased casserole in layers, asparagus, sliced eggs, alternately.
Cover with sauce and bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: light and easy lemon chicken
directions: You will need a 9 x 12-inch sheet of foil.

title: goulash
directions: Brown meat and onion until done.
Add all other ingredients. Cook until noodles are done.

title: creamy tuna rice
directions: Bring water, milk, dill and salt to a boil in a medium saucepan on medium heat.
Add cheese; cook and stir until cheese is melted.

title: rice and spinach deluxe casserole
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in melted margarine until tender. Follow thawing instructions on spinach box and drain.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole combine spinach, cooked rice, melted cheese spread, onions and mushrooms. Stir in soup.
Add nutmeg.
Cook at 350°, covered, for 35 to 40 minutes, stirring occasionally until heated thoroughly.
Yields 6 servings.

title: italian beef
directions: Cook roast in crock-pot overnight, 7 to 8 hours, on high (add 2 cups water, salt and pepper to taste).
Take meat out and slice into small pieces.
Add onion gravy mix, oregano and garlic to broth left in crock-pot.
Make sure all gravy mix is dissolved. Return beef to crock-pot and cook on low for 2 to 3 hours.
Serve on hard rolls.

title: dream cake
directions: Mix gelatin with cold water.
Add boiling water and mix well. Add pineapple, sugar, salt and lemon juice.
Mix well and let stand until it starts to thicken.
Fold in 2 envelopes of Dream Whip prepared according to package directions.
Line a large cake pan with plastic wrap.
Put alternate layers of mixture and angel food cake that has been torn in small pieces, making cake the first layer and last layer.
Cover with plastic wrap and leave in refrigerator overnight.
Unmold next day and ice with 1 prepared envelope of Dream Whip.
Sprinkle with angel flake coconut.

title: who dun-its
directions: You will need 6 squares of heavy-duty foil.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini.
Add all dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Yields 2 large or 6 small loaves.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate cheese and soften.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Use half of the mixture for 1 ball.
Recipe makes a 2 pound ball.

title: sausage strata
directions: Butter and line 9 x 13-inch pan with bread slices.
Fry sausage, drain and place evenly over bread slices. Cover with cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients together and pour over bread, sausage and cheese mixture.
Chill overnight.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: pork pie
directions: Cook pork, onions and cloves in water until water is gone. Mix cooked pork with mashed potatoes.
Put into pie plate with crust. Top with remaining crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Fry sausage until done.
Drain. Separate 8 crescent rolls into triangles on ungreased 12-inch pizza pan, points to the center. Seal perforations.
Bring dough up the sides.
Sprinkle on sausage, potatoes and Cheddar cheese. Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over everything.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Toast pecans at 350° for 15 minutes.
Place in unbaked pie shell.
Blend flax seed with 1/4 cup warm water.
Add 1/2 to 3/4 cup water as it thickens while blending.
Pour mixture into bowl.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Cook cubed sweet potatoes in water for 15 minutes until tender.
Drain well and cool.
Put potatoes and applesauce in food processor until smooth.
Add egg yolk, vanilla and cinnamon; process until smooth.
Spoon into bowl and set aside.
Beat egg whites at room temperature until stiff peaks.
Gently stir 1/3 of egg whites into sweet potato mixture, then gently fold in remaining egg whites.
Spoon into 1/2-quart souffle coated with spray.
Combine sugar, flour and margarine.
Sprinkle over potatoes.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: coffee can ice cream
directions: Pour mixture into 1 pound coffee can.
Place inside 3 pound coffee can or No. 10 can with plastic lid.
Fill with ice and ice cream salt.
Cover with lid.
Roll on ground or floor 15 minutes. Serves 4.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Grate potatoes and put them in the 2 cups of milk so they won't turn dark.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and put into large baking dish.
Butter casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: cousin kay's 7-layer bars
directions: Dissolve jello in water and chill.
When slightly thickened, add pineapple and sour cream and mix well in blender.
Pour into decorative bowl and chill.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs; blend sugar and flour and stir in eggs.
Add all remaining ingredients in order listed and place into 2 greased 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: In a large pot, boil hamburger, onion, potatoes, peas, and salt and pepper to taste.
Boil until potatoes are cooked.
Cover hamburger mixture with biscuit dough.
Bake according to instructions on biscuits.

title: salad dressing
directions: Combine flour and sugar; mix well.
Beat egg; add to flour/sugar.
Add vinegar and reserved pineapple juice.
Cook in small pan on low heat.
Stir and cook until thick.
Pour cooled dressing over apples, pineapple and peanuts.
Mix in Cool Whip. May sprinkle additional peanuts over top for garnish.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: marlys's quick and easy chocolate cake
directions: On stove, bring first 3 ingredients to a boil. Using hand mixer, add next 7 ingredients. Pour batter into a greased rectangular cake pan or use 2 square pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Frost cake while hot.

title: cioppino
directions: In a heavy kettle or large pot, melt butter and olive oil. Drop in garlic, onions, green onions and peppers; simmer until tender.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and all of the spices mixed together; stir to mix.
Add the rock codfish.
Cook for 9 hours very slowly, then add wine and cook 30 minutes longer.
Add the clams with their shells on, then the cracked crab, shrimp and scallops.
Cook the shellfish in the sauce for 30 minutes, then serve with hot, garlic buttered bread.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in boiling, salted water for 5 minutes and drain.
Combine soup, Cheddar cheese and sour cream.
Stir in shredded carrots, then fold in squash and onion mixture.
Combine stuffing mix and melted margarine and add nutmeg and Bell seasoning.
Spread half of the stuffing mix in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Alternate layers of vegetables and stuffing mix, ending with stuffing.
Place a few small pats of unmelted margarine on top for a more moist consistency.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop the corn.
Put into a bowl. Add nuts.
In 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, brown sugar, corn syrup, water, vinegar and salt.
Heat to a boil on medium-high heat, stirring constantly. Cook and stir until 260° on candy thermometer.
Reduce heat to low. Stir in butter until melted.
Pour syrup over corn and nuts in thin stream, stirring until coated. Spread on buttered sheet to cool.
Enjoy!

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Slowly add beaten eggs into dry ingredients and add oil also.
Stir in crushed corn.
Drop by tablespoon onto lightly greased skillet. Fry until golden brown.

title: caramel corn(amish recipe)
directions: Bring first three ingredients to a boil and pour over popped corn.
Heat in oven for 1 hour at 250°.
Stir often.

title: cran-scrumptious punch
directions: Mix in punch bowl in order listed.

title: beef roast with corn meal dumplings
directions: Brown beef roast (chuck roast works well) in oil.
Mix water, dried onion soup mix, thyme and diced celery.
Pour over roast. Cover and cook slowly 2 hours or until tender.
Mix dumplings and drop in by spoonfuls.
Cover tightly and steam for 15 minutes. Thicken liquid for gravy, if desired.

title: dine on the run
directions: Drive to your nearest McDonald's and order what you like.

title: cranberry casserole
directions: Combine apples, cranberries and granulated sugar in a casserole dish.
Melt margarine in a skillet.
Add oatmeal, brown sugar, flour and pecans.
Pour over apple mixture.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: country corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease and dust skillet with cornmeal. Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour mixture into skillet and bake until golden brown.

title: german chocolate upside down cake
directions: Melt margarine and pour in 9 x 13 in. pan.
Press in coconut and pecans.
Mix cake mix by directions on box.
Pour over pecans and coconut.
Mix powdered sugar and cream cheese together.
Spoon over cake. Bake at 450 degrees for 45 min.

title: little red hens
directions: Sprinkle neck and body cavity of each chicken with monosodium glutamate and salt.
Stuff with Walnut Stuffing.
Hook wing tips onto back to hold neck skin.
Tie legs together and then to tail. Place chickens in shallow roasting pan (it is unnecessary to use rack).
Roast 1 1/2 hours at 375°.
Brush with Cranberry-Orange Glaze. Roast 15 minutes longer.
Yields 8 servings.
Contains 350 calories per serving.

title: magic crust fruit cobbler
directions: Mix together; put in small deep Pyrex casserole.
Cover thickly with fruit; fruit sinks to bottom during cooking.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Any fruit may be used.
Serves 4.

title: southwestern cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients; cream butter, eggs, vanilla and syrup.
Mix buttermilk with bananas.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk/bananas.
Add walnuts and dates.
Bake in two nine-inch cake pans (floured and greased). Bake at 350° until done.
Cool and top with Penuche Icing.

title: buttermilk cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Separately, mix warm buttermilk, salt, soda, ;sugar and cooking oil.
Add yeast and mix.
Pour this over flour.
Knead 5 minutes.
Cover and rest 10 minutes.
Roll out and sprinkle with soft margarine or butter, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle with raisins or chopped walnuts, if desired.
Roll and slice.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar icing when partially cooled. Serve warm, if desired.
Delicious!

title: cheese puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter, in mixer until smooth. Cut bread in small rounds with cutter (about 1 1/2-inch diameter). Cover one round with spread, then top with another round of bread.
Cover with spread on top and sides as if icing a cake. Place all "iced" rounds on cookie sheet and freeze.
When frozen, can be transferred to a plastic bag and kept in freezer until ready to bake.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes about 50 to 60.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add Crisco, eggs and applesauce.
Mix well and then stir in nuts, raisins, etc.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan or similar size.
Bake for 1 hour and 25 to 35 minutes at 350° or in a loaf pan for 1 hour.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown beef, cool and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to the cooled beef.
Spoon onto sliced buns, cover and wrap in foil.
Keep in freezer.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel and core apple; cut into 8 slices.
Separate roll dough. Place 1 slice of apple on each roll.
Wrap to enclose apple. Arrange in baking dish; sprinkle with apple pie spice.
Combine orange juice, sugar and margarine in saucepan.
Cook until butter is melted and sugar is dissolved.
Pour over rolls.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage snacks
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on cookie sheet with vegetable spray.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pork special
directions: Cut pork chops in cubes and sprinkle the cubes with salt and pepper.
Fry the cubes in oil until nice and brown.
Once almost brown, fry with the meat for a minute, garlic, carrots and leek. Add beef-tea and soy sauce.
Simmer for another 15 minutes. Thicken the sauce with peanut butter.
Serve with white rice.

title: einstein's cranberry salad
directions: Grind the raw cranberries and add sugar.
Let stand until juice forms.
When the juice forms, add the apples, bananas, marshmallows and nuts.
Stir into mixture the whipped cream. Chill for 1 hour.

title: jill's chicken pot pie
directions: Pour in 1 (9-inch) pie shell and put other shell on top. Crimp edges; cut slits.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: beef tips with rice
directions: Brown meat.
Place in pan with tight-fitting lid.
Pour mushroom soup and 1 can of water over meat.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over the meat.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours. Be sure that the lid fits closely to retain juice.
Do not stir.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops, slice potatoes and add to pork chops.
Cover with water and add mushroom soup.
Put pork chops on top of potatoes.
Cover and bake at 450° for about 1 hour or until pork chops and potatoes are done.

title: pot roast
directions: Place vegetables and meat in slow cooker.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Dissolve bouillon cube in water and then pour over other ingredients.
Cover and cook on low 10-12 hours.

title: quick yeast muffins
directions: Mix yeast and water; add egg, oil, sugar, salt and flour. Grease muffin pans and bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
This batter will keep one week in the refrigerator.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix and freeze according to freezer directions.

title: ham, cheese squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Spread evenly in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut into squares. Garnish with apple slices.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken tortillas
directions: Debone chicken.
Cut into large pieces; set aside.
In a bowl, combine onions, the soups and milk, blending well.
In a 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole, layer half tortillas, chicken, sauce and cheese.
Sprinkle with the green chilies.
Repeat the layers once more until all ingredients are used, ending with cheese on top.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Remove cover.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
tags: cream of mushroom and cream of chicken soups

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix the ingredients, then arrange pecans on bottom of an 8-inch pie crust.
Gently pour egg mixture over pecans.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.
Pie should be firm when it's done.

title: italian cream cake and cream cheese icing
directions: Combine soda and buttermilk and let stand a few minutes.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Cream sugar, oleo and Crisco.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add buttermilk alternately with flour to creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.
Gently stir in pecans and coconut. Bake in three 9-inch greased and floured layer
pans at 325° for 25 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool before frosting with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Spread sauerkraut in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange tomato slices over sauerkraut; spread with salad dressing and dot with butter.
Top with corned beef and cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Separate each biscuit into 3 thin layers; arrange over casserole.	Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and caraway seeds.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: italian style carrots
directions: Heat skillet to a moderate to high heat; add olive oil.
Add carrots; stir regularly and cook 10 minutes.
Add garlic and salt. Cook 10 minutes over low heat.
Add olives; stir.
Serve at room temperature.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Fill jars with cucumbers.
Boil vinegar and other ingredients. Pour over cucumbers and seal.
Put in freezer.

title: chicken wok-style
directions: In your wok or skillet, heat oil and saute onion with garlic. When onion is tender, add meat and cook until no pink is left. Add spice and Worcestershire sauce to this mixture and stir, adding frozen veggies.
Pour in 1 1/2 cups of water and cover for 15 minutes on medium heat.
Add chestnuts and any fresh veggies and stir.
Cover and allow to cook until veggies are done, but not mushy.
Push mixture to sides of pan, allowing liquid to collect in a nice size circle.
To this, add the rice and cover.
When rice is tender, stir.
Serve over noodles or mashed potatoes. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Spray 9 x 5 loaf pan. Put layer of Fritos. Unwrap tamales and place layer of tamales. Add onions, then peppers, then layer of cheese. Heat chili and pour over cheese. Add layer of Fritos. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: gertrude armstrong
directions: Mix flour and sugar together in a mixing bowl and set aside. In a saucepan, melt the oleo, cocoa and water together and bring to a full boil.
Pour over the sugar and flour mixture and add buttermilk,
eggs
baking soda and
vanilla and pour batter into a greased 16 x 11-inch pan (cookie sheet) and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Split rolls.
Mix butter, mustard, poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Spread on split rolls.
Layer ham and cheese. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: apricot bars
directions: In a large bowl, cream the butter and sugar. Add egg and mix well. In a separate bowl, combine flour and baking powder. Gradually add to butter mixture. Add nuts, coconut and vanilla. Mix well.
Press 2/3 of the dough into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Spread preserves on top. Crumble remaining dough on top of preserves.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown.
Cool on wire rack. Cut into 36 squares.
(A rich, delicious cookie.)

title: broiled coconut frosting
directions: Mix together.
Spread over warm cake.
Brown under broiler. Watch carefully to prevent burning.

title: peanut butter cereal bars
directions: Heat sugar and honey in large boiler until sugar melts. Remove from heat.
Add the peanut butter; mix well.
Stir in the corn flakes; coat thoroughly.
Pour the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole sprayed with Pam.
Pat the mixture into the pan until it is almost smooth.
Let cool; cut into squares.

title: fiesta corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Melt shortening in 8 or 9-inch pan. Combine dry ingredients.
Add melted shortening and remaining ingredients.
Mix until blended.
Pour into prepared pan and bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: texas cake
directions: Mix together and heat to boiling the first 4 ingredients.
In bowl, put flour and sugar.
Pour boiling mix in bowl; add buttermilk, eggs, salt, baking soda and vanilla.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: Mix all
together in large skillet with small amount of bacon grease.
Fry for 3 to 4 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit, but save 1 1/2 cups of juice (except for peach or pear juice).
If not enough juice, add water to make 1 1/2 cups. Mix juice with pudding.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add fruit except for bananas and cherries.
Do not add bananas or cherries until ready to serve.
Store in refrigerator.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Place the crust in a quiche dish.
Arrange apples in crust. Mix the 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over apples.
Mix flour and 1/3 cup sugar.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and partially thaw Tater Tots.
In bottom of casserole dish, put one layer of Tater Tots (half of package). Put layer of hamburger, then a layer of green beans and half of cheese.
Layer remaining green beans and hamburger with remaining Tater Tots on top.
Dilute mushroom soup with 1 soup can milk. Pour over casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Place remaining cheese on top of casserole and melt in oven.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Cook spinach in boiling water and salt for 10 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
In pan, melt Crisco.
Add flour to make a roux. Add milk and cook until mixture thickens.
Add spinach; stir thoroughly and heat.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream the cheese and juice with mixer.
Add remaining ingredients except paprika and nuts.
Mold into ball.
Roll in paprika or cover with crushed nuts.
Chill well.
Serve at room temperature.

title: barbecue pork
directions: Mix ingredients in a crock-pot.
Let cook about 6 hours or until tender.
Shred meat.
Makes about 20 sandwiches.

title: dream cake
directions: Mix butter, flour and the 1/4 cup brown sugar.
Spread in 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread on top of the first mixture and return to oven for about 20 minutes or until brown.
Cut into 9 pieces.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Drain beans and pour in casserole.
Cook bacon and onion in large skillet until brown.
Add ketchup, brown sugar and vinegar. Cook until it boils, then add to beans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn bread stuffing
directions: Simmer minced onion in butter in large skillet until tender. Combine in a bowl cornbread crumbs, salt, poultry seasoning, celery seed, minced parsley and pepper.
Add to onion mixture and heat well without browning. Stir frequently.
This makes enough for a 4 pound bird.

title: chicken beer bake
directions: Remove skin from chicken; wash chicken and dry well with paper towels.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge chicken in flour mixture and brown in heated oil.
Place chicken in a shallow pan. Combine soup, soy sauce, 2 tablespoons almonds, beer and mushrooms; pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour, basting occasionally.
Sprinkle with remaining almonds.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mountain pie
directions: Melt butter or margarine in 3-quart baking dish.
Add all other ingredients, except fruit, and stir.
Add fruit and bake. Use blackberries or peaches.
If the fruit isn't sweet enough, add more sugar.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and bananas.
Sift dry ingredients together; add buttermilk and vanilla.
Fold in chopped nuts.
Combine 2 mixtures.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 325° to 350° for 1 hour or until bread tests done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Boil, skin and bone chicken.
Break into pieces.
Mix all ingredients except chicken, cheese and potato chips.
Layer bottom of large shallow buttered casserole dish with chicken.
Spoon mixture over chicken.
Top with cheese and potato chips.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Sift first 5 dry ingredients together in a bowl. Mix oleo, Sugar Twin and egg. Mix in dry ingredients alternately with applesauce. Fold in bran, raisins and nuts. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Flatten lightly. Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Heat the oil in a large saucepan and add the garlic and onions.
Cook, stirring until the onions are light brown.
Add the tomatoes, tomato puree, tomato paste, water and seasonings. Simmer for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Leftover sauce may be frozen.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Separate eggs.
Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl, excluding egg whites.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 375° for an additional 15 minutes.
Turn oven off; let pie stay in oven for 5 minutes.
Chill and serve.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: beef and corn casserole
directions: Put shortening in skillet and saute peppers and onion for 3 minutes.
Add meat and blend in salt and pepper.
Remove from heat and stir in eggs.
Mix well.
Place 1 cup of corn in greased casserole dish.
Spread some meat on top, then add a layer of sliced tomatoes.
Repeat procedure until dish is full.
Top with dry bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: paprika potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and cut in half.
Allow to drain on a paper towel.
In a large (13 x 9-inch) pan, pour enough oil to make 1/8 to 1/4-inch layer in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle heavily with paprika (oil should be evenly covered).
Repeat with remainder of spices. Place cut side of potatoes face down into oil.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: bread sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Use "day-old" hot dog or hamburger buns.
Butter all sides of buns.
Cut into pieces.
Sprinkle garlic salt over bread.
Bake 15 minutes in a 300° oven.
Take out and turn bread over and bake another 10 minutes.
Turn oven off. Leave in oven for 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Saute the onion in oil until clear but not brown. Chop and mash the avocados and add to this the hard-boiled eggs which have been finely chopped. Add the onion with the oil in which it was cooked. Fold in the mayonnaise and stir all ingredients until well mixed. Serve chilled.

title: carolina's onion rings
directions: Slice onion.
Dip slices in milk, then coat with flour.
Fry in deep fat in frying pan until brown and crisp.

title: louisiana pear pie
directions: Place pears in a saucepan and add a little water.
Cook until almost tender.
Mix dry ingredients and add to pears.
Stir lightly to mix.
Pour filling into pastry.
Dot with butter and place top crust on pie, sealing the edges.
Make 3 or 4 slits in top crust.
Bake at 400 degrees for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: potato ham skillet
directions: In a large skillet, combine the potatoes, ham, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir over medium low heat until heated through.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Serves 4.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for at least 1 hour.

title: artichoke dipfort morgan, colorado
directions: Stir all ingredients.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake in oven at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add liquids and mix until smooth.
Pour into greased oblong pan. Bake approximately 35 minutes at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all except bacon in a casserole dish. Put bacon strips on top.
Bake at 300° for about 45 minutes.

title: easy rolls
directions: Press the biscuits into a greased pan with butter.
Put buttered side up.
Press a small hole in biscuits and fill with pie filling.
Mix 3 tablespoons flour and sugar together.
Spread on top of biscuits.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: apple cinnamon shake
directions: Blend in blender.
Each serving contains 70 calories.

title: kathryn's favorite broccoli casserole
directions: Wash broccoli.
Cut off florets and cut into dipping size pieces.
Spread these evenly onto the bottom of a shallow casserole (2-quart) dish.
Cook in microwave oven on High for 4 to 5 minutes (you may steam broccoli, then put into dish).
In a medium size mixing bowl, beat the eggs.
Add soup and mayonnaise; beat together until well mixed.
Mix milk in well.
Fold in cheese and onion.
Pour this mixture over the broccoli; spread evenly. Bake for 45 to 55 minutes in a 350° oven (until is browning and the center is fairly firm to the touch).
Goes well with chicken baked in the same oven.

title: corned beef dip
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together with electric beater. Mix will be stiff but will soften at room temperature.
Serve with veggies or crackers.

title: pork chop skillet meal
directions: In a large skillet, brown chops in oil; drain. Remove chops.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs well and set aside.
Mix sugar, flour, butter together and add to eggs.
Last add milk.
Bake in pie shell for 250° or 30 minutes at 375°.

title: rolls
directions: Heat
milk.
Do
not
boil.
Pour over shortening, salt and sugar.
Let
cool at least to lukewarm before adding 1 cup of flour.
Dissolve
yeast
in
warm water.
Add to above mixture. Break
egg
into
yeast's
cup (after yeast
has
been dumped). Beat egg and add to above mixture and mix
well; add remaining 1 1/2 cups of flour.
Turn out and knead
well, then return to the bowl you mixed batter in that has
been buttered (you don't have to wash it).
Cover with cloth and let rise in warm place until double in bulk.

title: cashew candy
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, water and cream of tartar.
Cook and stir until sugar dissolves.
Bring to boiling point, boil until syrup reaches hard crack stage of 300°.
Remove from heat; stir in cashews and vanilla.
Set pan in larger pan of hot water to keep soft.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased baking sheet or wax paper to form clusters.

title: hot wiener sauce
directions: Brown meat; drain grease.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.

title: bazillions of beans
directions: In a large roaster for stove top, cut up and fry bacon.
Add onions and fry.
Add hamburger and remaining ingredients.
You can add any other beans you want.
Simmer on stove 1 hour.
Tastes better the next day.
Serve with French bread or corn bread.

title: cajun creole seasoning
directions: Mix all; keep in a dry jar.
Use in place of salt.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, onions and salt in water until tender.
Add pepper, butter and milk; bring to a boil.
Serve hot.

title: mom's oreo dessert
directions: Line crumbled Oreos on the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice vanilla ice cream and place on top of crumbled Oreos.
(Put in freezer while mixing the following.)
Put 4 ounces chocolate squares, evaporated milk, butter and sugar in saucepan.
Boil for 4 minutes.
Remove from heat, add vanilla and let cool.
Pour over ice cream and freeze before serving.
Take out of freezer a few minutes before serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with onion (use 2 cups cooked squash).
Mix with cream
of
celery
soup
and
sour cream.
Mix package of Pepperidge	Farm
stuffing	mix
with
stick melted butter. Layer
squash,
dressing
mix, squash and dressing mix on top. Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Coat tomato slices with flour, dip into egg seasoned with salt and pepper, then into bread crumbs, brown on both sides in lightly oiled skillet over medium heat.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and serve hot.

title: crabbies
directions: Spread mixture on muffin halves and freeze 15 to 20 minutes. Cut into fourths and bag them to freeze.
Bake at 350° to 400° on cookie sheet for 10 to 15 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: pizza twist
directions: Separate and unroll breadsticks.
Place 3 pepperoni slices in a single layer over 1/2 of each breadstick.
Fold remaining half of breadstick over top.
Seal and twist into a figure 8.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Combine cheese, Italian seasoning and garlic powder.
Sprinkle evenly over each breadstick.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or golden brown.
Serve with salsa, dip, pizza sauce or just plain.

title: peanut butter snack
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter.
Add sugar and cinnamon. Pour over cereal and mix.
Bake in two 9 x 13-inch pans at 250° to 300° for about 35 to 40 minutes (stir 3 to 4 times).

title: cheese-stuffed bread
directions: In a 12-inch skillet
over
medium heat, in hot butter, cook next 4
ingredients
until vegetables are tender.
Remove from heat.
Meanwhile,
cut
Italian
bread in half crosswise. Hollow out each half, leaving a 1/4-inch shell.
Crumble bread in
large bowl.
Beat
cream
cheese
until
smooth;
stir
in pimentos, red pepper, cabbage mixture and bread crumbs.
Pack mixture
into hollowed
out crust.
Wrap tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerate until mixture is firm, at least 4 hours.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Butter an angel food cake pan.
Pop popcorn and sift to get rid of unpopped corn.
Melt margarine and marshmallows; remove from heat and add peanuts and a cup of gumdrops.
Stir with large spoon and pour over popcorn until popcorn is covered.
Wet hands with cold water and pack well into angel food cake pan until firm. Let stand in pan for 3 hours, then take out and wrap in wax paper or store in cake container.

title: hishy-hash and a hell-an-a stew
directions: Use fresh peppers from garden.
Use some that have turned red for color contrast.
Dice leftover boiled potatoes.
Brown hamburger; drain.
Saute onion, green pepper and hot pepper.
Add potatoes and brown.
Return hamburger and brown a little more, stirring all together constantly.
Whisk eggs.
Pour over top of meat mixture.
Brown until egg is cooked.

title: cider basted chicken
directions: In shallow dish, combine all ingredients and marinate overnight turning occasionally.
Pour off marinade and reserve for basting.
Arrange chicken in pan and bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes or until done.
Baste with marinade every 10 minutes.

title: bunny cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, sift sugar and flour with baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Make a well in the center.
Add eggs, oil, nuts, vanilla, pineapple and mashed bananas.
Stir together (do not beat).

title: special cake
directions: Pour crushed pineapple with juice into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with coconut and pecans.
Spread dry cake mix over the mixture.
Place squares of margarine over entire top of cake. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: pickle relish
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and let stand for three hours.
Drain and squeeze vegetables dry and add to liquid.
Simmer 20 minutes. Pack and seal in hot jars.

title: easy chicken and noodles
directions: Cook chicken breasts; cut meat from bones in chunks.
Reserve broth.
Mix cream of chicken soup with enough broth to make creamy; add the chicken chunks and a few good dashes of parsley flakes.
Cook the noodles in the remaining chicken broth plus water until done.
Mix noodles with the chicken soup sauce.
Add salt to taste.
Bake for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: sweet cornbread
directions: Mix and pour into greased rectangular baking pan. Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: superb baked scallops
directions: Combine all ingredients except green onions and butter.
Place in casserole.
Top with onions and butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: mother's chocolate cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in 350° oven until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter and mix in bread crumbs and moisten crumbs with a little of the chicken broth.
Put half of the crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put cooked chicken in pan on top of crumbs.
In a bowl, mix sour cream, soup and chicken broth together.
Put on top of chicken.
Put rest of moistened bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pat's top cobbler
directions: Put pie filling in baking plate and top with cake mix.
Top with melted margarine and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Serve with Cool Whip on top if desired.

title: boiled custard
directions: Use heavy saucepan.
When the 3 cups milk have reached the scalding point, remove from heat and stir in sugar and 4 well beaten eggs; then the whipping cream.
Return to heat and cook, stirring constantly, until the mixture coats a wooden spoon.

title: louisiana style oyster po-boys
directions: At least 1/2 hour before using, drain oysters.
Dredge with corn meal, salt and pepper.
In large skillet, pour 3 inches of oil.
Heat to 390°.
Gently lower oysters and deep fry until golden.
Drain on absorbent paper and keep warm.

title: good refrigerator rolls
directions: Cream sugar, salt, shortening and eggs.
Add cold and hot water, 2 cups flour and yeast mixture.
Beat well.
Gradually add remaining flour; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.
Use as needed. Shape and let rise for about 1 hour.
Bake at 400° until brown. This mixture will keep up to 2 weeks stored in refrigerator.

title: tuna salad
directions: Boil eggs; peel and chop.
Prepare macaroni according to instructions.
Drain, rinse and drain again.

title: christmas salad
directions: Soak gelatin in water; heat pineapple and dissolve gelatin; cool.
Add cranberries, lemon juice, celery and nuts.
Chill until set.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon into a large bowl.
In another bowl, beat eggs; add sugar, oil and vanilla. Make a well in the flour mixture.
Pour in oil and eggs.
Stir until all is
moistened.
Fold in carrots, dates, walnuts, coconut and apple.
Don't overmix.

title: butterscotch candy
directions: Stir ingredients together and cook without stirring to the hard-crack stage (dropped from a spoon into ice cold water and breaks between fingers when cool).
Turn into a large buttered baking sheet, making a thin layer.
When partly cooled, mark in squares or when cold, break in pieces with handle of knife.

title: rigatoni supreme
directions: Cook veal with parsley, carrot and bay leaf for approximately 1 hour in enough water to cover veal.
Add more water if needed. Drain and reserve stock.
Put salt pork in cold water and heat to boil without lid.
Boil 2 minutes to get rid of excess salt.
Cut in small pieces and saute in olive oil.
Add green onion, Prosciutto, artichoke hearts and cooked veal and saute until green onions are limp and cooked, about 3 minutes.
Add tomato paste, sherry and veal stock and mix well.
Simmer 7 minutes.

title: chocolate banana split
directions: Pour milk into medium bowl.
Add pudding mix; beat with wire whisk or mixer for 1 to 2 minutes.
Spoon pudding evenly into 4 dessert dishes.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Halve and split bananas just before serving.
Place 2 pieces in each dish. Top each serving with 2 tablespoons whipped topping.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine filling ingredients in order given; pour into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake an additional 45 minutes or until knife inserted near center of pie comes out clean.
Cool; garnish, if desired, with whipped topping.

title: light and flaky danish puff
directions: Cut the first 2 ingredients together.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons water over mixture.
Roll into ball; divide in half.
On ungreased baking sheet, pat each half into a 12 x 3-inch strip.
Strips should be 3 inches apart.
Heat to a rolling boil the oleo and 1 cup water.
Remove from heat and quickly stir in almond extract and 1 cup flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat until the mixture forms a ball.
Beat in 3 eggs all at once until smooth and glossy. Divide in half; spread evenly over strips to edges.
Bake 60 minutes until brown.
Cool.

title: bulviniai bynai(potato pancakes)
directions: Peel, then grate potatoes and onion.
Add salt, pepper, beaten eggs and flour.
This will make a very loose batter.
In a cast-iron skillet, heat enough Crisco to just reach the top of pancake.
Ladle a large spoonful of batter onto hot shortening and cook on one side of pancake until brown and crisp.
Turn pancake over and brown on other side likewise.
Remove from fat.
Serve with sour cream and applesauce.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Combine mayonnaise and ketchup; mix well.
Add rest of ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Pour into a glass covered jar and refrigerate.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Using a knife, mix sugar and Karo syrup in medium size bowl. Cook on High power for 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts and butter. Cook on High power for 4 more minutes.
While stirring, add soda and vanilla.
Spread on a lightly buttered cookie sheet.
