Candy will begin to harden almost immediately, so you must work quickly.

title: old-fashioned rice custard
directions: In the top
of a double boiler, combine rice and 2 cups milk. Cook,
stirring
occasionally, over boiling water until rice is tender
and most of the water has evaporated, about 45 minutes. Stir in butter.
Beat eggs; blend in sugar, vanilla, salt and
the remaining milk.
Stir into the hot rice mixture. Pour into
a lightly
greased
2-quart casserole and top with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until firm.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: marinated sausage balls
directions: Make 1-inch sausage balls; brown and drain.
Mix other ingredients for marinade.
Place sausage balls in marinade and refrigerate until needed.
Good cold or at room temperature.
Cook in small amount of oil until done.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Grease	pan.
Put
nuts
and
coconut in bottom of pan. Mix cake
according
to
directions.
Pour
cake
batter over mixture in	pan.
Beat the cream cheese with one stick butter. Add the confectioners
sugar.
Add the egg; mix well and pour over cake. Bake for 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: dutch cheese wafers
directions: *These are optional. Can be plain, fruit on top or between 2.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt
margarine and let cool.
Beat eggs, add sugar and beat well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Add margarine last.
Mix well. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Drain tuna and break into bite-size pieces.
Mix mushroom soup, water and soy sauce.
Combine tuna, mushroom soup mixture, cashew nuts, mushrooms, onion, celery and 1 cup of the noodles. Pour into a 1-quart casserole.
Cover and refrigerate.
About 55 minutes before serving time, heat oven to 375°.
Sprinkle remaining 1 cup noodles over casserole and bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: pan pizza
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add pizza sauce.
Layer:
macaroni, cheese, peppers, onion, olives, mushrooms, pepperoni and more cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake in preheated oven about 10 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix all together and make rolls.
Place in greased pan and let rise to desired size (30 to 40 minutes).
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat 3 to 4 minutes until batter is smooth and fluffy.
Put in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes until cake pulls away from edge of pan.

title: carol's favorite spiced pork chops
directions: Wash pork and vegetables first.
Cook pork chops in pan on medium heat until nicely brown on both sides.
Gently place pork in ungreased rectangular baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper.
Arrange onion rings, squash rings and neatly sliced apple rings on pork chops.
Place potatoes around sides of dish.

title: chocolatey hot cocoa
directions: Measure and whisk all ingredients into a bowl. Cover tightly and store until needed. Spoon 3 or 4 rounded tablespoonfuls into cup. Add boiling water. Stir.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook chicken, strain and save to make 6 cups.
Add 3 bouillon cubes or more to the boiling broth.
Saute onions (chopped) in oil and add to broth.
Add salt, garlic powder and cooked, chopped broccoli to broth.
Add water to cornstarch and stir into broth. Simmer, then add milk and cubed Velveeta.
Next, add cut up chicken.

title: mary's tofu pie
directions: Mix all together with electric beater.
Pour into pie crust and refrigerate.
Poke air holes with toothpicks.

title: salmon mousse
directions: Heat tomato soup.
Add dissolved gelatin.
Let cool.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix very well until completely blended.
Pour into 2-quart mold and chill.
Serve with crackers for appetizer. May also be used on lettuce leaf for salad.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl put all except meat and cornflakes.
Mix well.
Add meat and mix.
Add cornflakes and mix until loaf hold its shape. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Reduce to 350° for 45 minutes.
Put lid on when top is brown.

title: spicy fried tofu
directions: First, press tofu by cutting to 1/2-inch slices and firmly patting out excess water with an absorbent towel.
Cut into small cubes.
Spray Pam on nonstick skillet or wok.
Add tofu; saute on high heat for 5 minutes, turning with spatula.
Reduce heat to medium.
Add turmeric; stir until tofu is yellow all over.
Add the other seasonings, stirring well between each addition. Increase heat.
Add soy sauce, stirring constantly.
Finally, add nutritional yeast or Parmesan cheese; mix well, sauteing until golden brown or until cheese melts.
Good hot or cold.
Serves 4 to 8.

title: copper pennies
directions: Slice carrots in rounds the thickness of a penny.
Cook just until tender in salted water.
Drain.
Arrange carrots, pepper and onions in layers in a bowl.
Heat vinegar and sugar with tomato soup, oil, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and salt just until sugar melts.
Pour over vegetables and marinate 1 hour, then refrigerate.
This will keep for several days in the refrigerator. The longer it marinates, the better.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Sprinkle salt over above ingredients, then pour ice water over and let stand 1 hour. Drain and rinse. Make the following dressing and pour hot over vegetables. Boil 1 c. sugar, 1/2 c. vinegar and 1/2 c. water. Keep in refrigerator until ready to use. Will keep several days.

title: hoppin john
directions: Cook rice.
Drain and rinse peas.
Slice scallions.
In large frying pan, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble bacon. Pour off all but 2 tablespoons fat.
Put the rice, peas, scallions, salt and pepper into pan and heat through, 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in bacon and serve.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and evaporated milk in heavy gauged 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan. Bring to full rolling boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy reaches 234°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching. Remove from heat; stir in chocolate morsels until melted. Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla. Beat until well blended; pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Top with nuts; cool at room temperature. Cut into squares. Makes 3 pounds.

title: spiced tea
directions: Bring to a boil the water and tea bags. Turn off fire. Remove tea bags. Add sugar, ground cloves and cinnamon. Also add pineapple juice, frozen orange juice and frozen lemonade. Return to heat and bring to a boil. Now, it's ready!

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Spread chicken breasts flat.
Fold cheese and ham slices to fit on top.
Fold breasts over filling and fasten edges with toothpicks.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Sift flour and salt into bowl.
Pour oil and milk into same measuring cup; do not stir.
Dump into flour mixture.
Stir lightly with fork.
Divide dough and roll out between 2 pieces of waxed paper.
Remove top paper and invert crust into pan.
Peel off remaining piece of paper.
Repeat with top crust.

title: my own salad dressing
directions: Mix and place in refrigerator.	Will keep for weeks.

title: kolaches
directions: Combine the milk, yeast and sugar in a large bowl.
Set aside in a warm place until rises to the top.
Stir.
Add salt, oil, beaten eggs and flour to make a soft dough.
Stir until fairly smooth on top and set aside for 10 minutes.
Cover and let rise for 30 minutes or until more than double in size.
Cut out dough the size of a small egg with a tablespoon.
Shape into small balls and place on a well-greased baking sheet 1 inch apart.
Brush with melted shortening and let rise in a warm place away from draft for 15 minutes.
Make a well in the center of each ball of dough and fill with a cooled fruit mixture.
Let rise again for 25 minutes. Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for 15 minutes or until a golden brown.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add milk and vanilla.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Bake in greased pan 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: glenda's slaw
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: strawberry season dessert
directions: Make wafers into crumbs.
Mix crumbs with 1/2 stick butter. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat 1 stick butter with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat again.
Spread over crumbs. Place strawberries over this mixture.
Spread whipped cream over berries.
Sprinkle additional crumbs over this.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Slice and serve.
Serves 12.

title: nutty yam bake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mash yams.
Add next 5 ingredients. Beat in milk and eggs.
Whip well with mixer.
Turn into a greased 3-quart casserole.
Combine next 3 ingredients and mix until crumbly.
Mix in walnuts and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over top of yams mixture.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar.
Let stand.
Beat eggs; add oil and vanilla.
Mix flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir alternately with apple mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: cheese and pineapple salad
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until thick and cool.
Note: Save juice off sliced pineapple and use for your 1 cup pineapple juice. Add pineapple to cooked mixture and top with grated cheese.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Pick out rocks and bad beans, soak overnight in water.
Drain, rinse, add water to cover, add onion and bay leaves, cook until tender.
In skillet, brown bulk sausage and break apart; add beans.
In skillet, place thinly sliced smoked sausage and simmer to remove grease, add to beans.
Take cup of beans and mash, return to beans and stir.
(This will thicken mixture.)
Add salt to taste.
Pour over cooked rice.

title: sweet potato loaf cake
directions: Sift 1 1/2 cups flour with other dry ingredients three times. Dust raisins and nuts with other 1/2 cup flour.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add potatoes and then egg yolks.
Add flour mixture and 1/2 cup milk.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Fold in beaten egg whites. Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: stir-fried chicken
directions: In small bowl, stir together corn syrup, water, soy sauce, sherry, cornstarch, garlic and ginger.
In a large skillet or wok, heat corn oil over medium-high heat.
Add chicken; cook.

title: sugar-free dark chocolate mousse
directions: Use double boiler or microwave; melt both chocolate and butter.
With electric mixer or wire whisk, whip cream in a chilled mixing bowl (non-metal) until cream starts to become fluffy.
Add cocoa, Splenda and vanilla to cream.
Continue to whip until cream forms soft peaks.
Gently fold into the melted chocolate.
Spoon into individual parfait glasses.
Chill one hour.

title: lemon box cake
directions: Mix together and spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream the sugar, shortening and eggs thoroughly together.
Stir in buttermilk, mashed bananas and flour, then stir in soda and fold in chopped nuts.
If using plain flour, use 2 teaspoons soda and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Bake in greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan for 50 to 60 minutes. Yields 1 loaf.

title: mince meat
directions: Cook 1 hour.
Cook slow and keep stirring as it burns real easy.

title: new zealand asparagus
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to boil.
Whisk in egg yolks and cook until thick at low temperature.
Stir in cream.
Steam asparagus.
Serve with sauce over top.

title: clams and cheese
directions: Simmer clams in lemon juice.
Drain but reserve liquid.
Blend onions, pepper, parsley and enough of the reserved liquid to make a spread.
Add this to the clams with butter and pepper.
Add bread crumbs and cheese and pour into two pie pans.
Cover with Parmesan cheese or add more sliced cheese, if you wish.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: garlic flavored pretzels
directions: Mix together dressing, oil and garlic powder in large bowl. Add pretzels and toss to coat.
Put on baking sheet and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven; return pretzels to bowl. Toss again and put back in oven for 10 minutes more.

title: bananas in sauce
directions: Mix together in saucepan: water, vinegar, sugar and eggs. Cook until thick.
Add butter and cool.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Whip eggs.
Add sugar, baking soda, margarine, flour, salt and rest of ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: bessie's buckeyes
directions: In a large bowl, mix butter, peanut butter and flavoring.
Add sugar, a little at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Roll into 3/4-inch balls and place on waxed paper on a cookie sheet. If mixture sticks to your hands, add a little more sugar.
Don't make it too dry.
Put balls in the freezer until very well chilled.
Melt wafers over hot water in double boiler.
Stirk toothpick in center of almost frozen or frozen balls.
Dip in chocolate; cover all but the top.
Let drip.
Place back on waxed paper.
Remove toothpick.
Repeat until all balls are dipped. When buckeyes come to room temperature, close hole.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: rhubarb bars
directions: Press 3/4 of crumb mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour rhubarb mixture over crumbs.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over rhubarb.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; sift soda, flour and baking powder.
Cream the butter and sugar thoroughly.
Then add egg yolks, one at a time, and the vanilla.
Turn mixer down to low speed and add the flour alternately with sour cream; fold in egg whites; pour into tube pan.
Bake 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Test with broomstraw.

title: tacos
directions: Brown meat, onion, green pepper, garlic salt, onion salt, cumin, garlic powder, pepper and oregano.
After browned, add sauce and paste.
Cook for 8 hours.
"The longer to cook, the better to taste."
In separate bowls dice up lettuce, onion, tomato, green pepper and cheese.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, spices and pumpkin.
Add evaporated milk and stir until mixture is smooth.
Pour into pie shell and bake in oven 35 to 45 minutes or until mixture is firm.
Makes 1 pie.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Let cukes soak in lime water 24 hours.
Stir often.
Wash well and drain.
Add vinegar, sugar and salt.
Let set 3 hours.
Add pickling spice.
Cook about 40 minutes until translucent.
Seal hot in hot jars.
Yields 5 quarts.

title: caramel glazed apple chunk cake
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
In mixer, blend oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add apples and pecans to dry ingredients.
Add orange juice and dry ingredients to mixer.
Blend.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef and garlic in small amount of fat.
Add tomato paste, tomatoes, salt, pepper and oregano.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook noodles as directed on package.

title: baked barbecue potatoes
directions: Combine and mix flour, salt and pepper. Arrange potatoes, onions, flour mixture and 1/2 of cheese in a shallow 2-quart casserole. Combine catsup, Worcestershire, hot pepper sauce and scalded milk. Mix and pour over potatoes. Dot with butter, diced bacon and remaining cheese. Bake, covered, at 375° for 45 minutes. Uncover and continue baking 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: christmas wine punch
directions: Heat together, but do not boil.
Serve hot.
May be mixed together early in the day, but do not heat until ready to serve.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine eggs, oil and sugar; mix thoroughly.
Add flour and apples alternately to mixture.
Add coconut and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sad cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and beat well.
Add Bisquick,
nut meats, coconut and vanilla.
Grease and flour a 9 x 12-inch pan; pour batter in and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli per directions on package.
Drain thoroughly. Place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Melt 1/2 stick of margarine with Velveeta cheese.
Pour Velveeta mixture on top of broccoli.
Crush Ritz crackers with rolling pin to bread crumb consistency.
Pour crackers on top of cheese.
Top crackers with 1/2 stick of melted margarine.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix above ingredients and press 2/3 in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Melt 1 can condensed milk and 1 cup chocolate chips together over low heat (stir well).
Pour over top and sprinkle remaining 1/3 over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Pour corn liquid into a bowl; add egg and biscuit mix, stirring until smooth.
Fold in corn and drop by spoonful into hot grease.
Fry until golden.
Serve with honey.
Serves 6.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together thoroughly the margarine, sugar and eggs.
In a separate bowl, sift together the flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Stir the dry ingredients into the first mixture. Roll dough into walnut-sized balls and roll in cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet at 375°.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Cook sausage in medium skillet over medium heat 7 minutes or until evenly browned, turning occasionally.
Add water.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Drain.
Allow sausage to stand at room temperature until cool enough to handle.
Heat oil in 5-quart Dutch oven over medium heat.
Cook and stir onion and garlic in oil 4 minutes or until onion is soft.

title: eclair cake
directions: Bring water and butter to a boil.
Add flour and stir until mixture leaves sides of pan.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat until well blended.
Spread into a greased 10 x 15-inch pan with sides.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: perfect quiche
directions: Combine cheese, chopped ham and green onions and put on the bottom of the unbaked crust.
Combine remaining ingredients. Add this to pie crust.
Bake in 350° oven for about 45 minutes, until center is puffy and nicely browned.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Marinate chicken in the ingredients overnight (in refrigerator).
Bake chicken with sauce in the oven (covered).
Cook for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: sunday night's egg foo young
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Fry in about 1/4 cup Crisco.
Divide into patties.
This will be juicy, but will fry more solid.
Serve with soy sauce and hot leftover pork gravy.

title: chili skillet supper
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper lightly.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper and chili powder; mix well.
Bring to boiling point. Gradually add in macaroni.
Cover and reduce heat.
Gently simmer for about 20 minutes or until macaroni is done.
Serves 4.

title: rigatoni con pepperoni
directions: Saute garlic and onion in olive oil, just until clear.
Add the tomatoes and pepperoni.
Saute until tomatoes cook down a bit (about 3 minutes).
Add the cream, salt and pepper.
Toss with the rigatoni and top with the cheese.
Serves 4.

title: clam casserole
directions: Combine in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scampi with red bell peppers and zucchini
directions: Melt butter in heavy large skillet over high heat.
Add bell peppers, zucchini, shallots and garlic.
Saute until shallots begin to soften, about 4 minutes.
Mix in capers.
Transfer mixture to a large baking dish or gratin dish. Can be made 4 hours ahead.
Cool completely. Cover and set aside.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Saute celery and onions in butter until tender. Combine cream cheese and soup. Heat mixture until cream cheese melts. Add peas and water chestnuts. Pour into casserole dish. Crumble crackers on top and drizzle with margarine. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flavoring and baking powder. Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate fondue
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler. Add whipping cream and flavoring.
Pour into fondue pot.
Dip fresh fruit or angel food cake.

title: broccoli onion deluxe
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions and drain.
In saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons butter; blend in flour, milk, salt and pepper. Cook until thick; blend in cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in vegetables.
Pour in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Mix the other 2 tablespoons of margarine with bread crumbs and put on top of casserole.
Bake 20 minutes, covered, in a 350° oven.
Remove top and bake 10 minutes or until crumbs are brown.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Crumble
yeast;
add
sugar, salt and water.
Mix; then add beaten
eggs,
1/2 the flour; add shortening and remaining flour; mix
well.
Let
rise for about 3 hours or more.
Punch down and make into rolls.
Place rolls on greased pan and let rise again before cooking at 400°.
Bake until golden brown.

title: pecan cake
directions: Put sugar, lard and eggs together.
Mix well and add baking powder, vanilla, flour and milk.
Stir well then add pecans.
Bake at 350°.

title: sour cream mini muffins
directions: In a medium bowl, thoroughly mix all ingredients. Fill miniature muffin tins with batter. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: holiday yams
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch; blend well.
Stir in orange juice, oleo and salt.
Simmer over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix meal, milk, oil, corn, eggs, soda and salt well in a bowl. Brown hamburger and onion
and drain.
Mix 2/3 of cheese with hamburger and onion until
moist.
Put
thin layer of meal mixture in a 13 x
9-inch
ungreased Pyrex.
Sprinkle hamburger and
onion over meal mixture.
Sprinkle
the
rest
of
grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: black magic cake
directions: Measure flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt.
Sift together into mixing bowl.
Make a well in these dry ingredients and add salad dressing, water and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into 2 greased 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Ice with chocolate icing.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Place pie shell in refrigerator for 30 minutes. Mix the eggs and butter until well combined. Add the vanilla and buttermilk and mix well. Combine the flour, sugar and salt and stir into the liquid. Pour the filling into the pie shell and bake for 40 to 45 minutes, until set and lightly browned. Let cool on a rack. It can be served warm, room temperature or cold. Makes 8 servings.

title: diane's spring garden vegetable pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook vegetables together until tender (5 to 10 minutes).
Butter large glass plate.
Mix in blender or hand mix Bisquick, milk, eggs and seasonings.
Bake approximately 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: play dough
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients thoroughly.
In a pan, boil and stir the remaining ingredients. After this has come to a boil, pour it over the dry ingredients and stir.
It will look a mess and be too hot to handle.
Let it set until it is cool enough to handle.
Knead until soft.
The trick to good play dough is in the kneading.
Store at room temperature in a Ziploc bag.

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on; cool and peel.
Add sour cream, salt and pepper to taste.
In nonstick pan, melt butter.
Add onions and shredded cheese.
After potatoes cool, grate them in bowl with mixture.
Put in buttered 13 x 9-inch glass Pyrex pan. Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked denver sandwich
directions: Trim crusts from bread.
Arrange 4 slices, buttered side down, in
8 or 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese, ham, green pepper and onion.
Place remaining slices, buttered side up,
on top of filling.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and pepper. Pour
over sandwiches in pan.
Press each one lightly.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add potato chips and almonds.
Then add flour.
Mix will be crumbly.
With hands, roll into balls.
Place on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press flat with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes only.

title: date nut bread
directions: Place dates and cherries in bowl.
Pour boiling water over them; let stand.
Beat egg until light and add sugar gradually. Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Stir in walnuts.
Add date and flour mixtures alternately to egg mixture. Stir in shortening and vanilla.

title: pumpkin cheese bread
directions: Combine sugar, cream cheese and margarine, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Blend in pumpkin.
Add combined dry ingredients, mixing just until moistened.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into two greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from pans.

title: chocolate sundae pie
directions: Heat milk and 1/2 cup water in double boiler with nutmeg.
Beat egg yolks with sugar and salt until light.
Pour the hot milk over the egg mixture; return to double boiler and cook until consistency of thick cream.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin which has been soaking 5 minutes in cold water.
Add vanilla.
Cool.
When cool and ready to set, beat with egg beater and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour this delicate fluffy mixture into baked pie shell.
Set in refrigerator.
When thoroughly cool, cover with the sweetened whipped cream and sprinkle top with grated chocolate.

title: tangy party meatballs
directions: Place meatballs with sauce in baking dish.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: garden vegetable pie
directions: Combine broccoli, onion, green pepper and cheese in the bottom of a greased 10-inch pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour over vegetable mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: beer pancakes
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Beat in next 3 items.
Add butter.
Add mix.
Beat until smooth.
Spoon out into saucer-size circles on a medium-hot griddle.
Makes 18 pancakes.

title: salad maurice
directions: Break lettuce into bite size pieces and place in salad bowl. Cut tomatoes into quarters or eighths and toss with lettuce. Add vinegar, oil, relish, Worcestershire Sauce, tabasco and eggs to mayonnaise. Add dressing and toss. Top with ham, chicken and cheese.

title: homemade tartar sauce
directions: Mix all together; cover and refrigerate.
Yields 3/4 cup sauce.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Place asparagus in casserole dish and layer, ending with cracker crumbs on top.
Dot with butter and juice of asparagus. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry surprise cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spread marshmallows across bottom.
Combine strawberries and juice with dry gelatin; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients; beat well.
Pour batter over marshmallows.
Spoon berry mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300°; bake for 15 minutes. Marshmallows will rise to the top.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a buttered casserole dish.
Top with potato chips.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 30 - 40 minutes.

title: leek and potato soup
directions: Put leeks, celery and butter in a pan.
Cook 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add water.
Cover and cook 10 more minutes. Add potatoes and add more water to cover.
Cover and cook 10 additional minutes.
Add milk.
Simmer until potatoes are tender. Season to taste with salt, pepper and cayenne.
Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: poached salmon with basil mayonnaise(makes 4 servings)
directions: Prepare Basil Mayonnaise.
Cover and set aside.

title: italian broccoli casserole
directions: Mix broccoli, eggs and soup in a shallow baking dish.
Place tomatoes on top.
Sprinkle cheese and oregano over all and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix soup, lemon juice and curry powder.
Place in a large greased 8 x 12-inch dish or pan.
Add a layer of broccoli, then chicken pieces and a layer of broccoli, and so on.
Spread soup over top, then the cheese.
Can cover with buttered breadcrumbs. Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Soak chicken breasts in salt water overnight.
Pour off water.
Cover chicken with salad dressing for a couple of hours. Place chicken breasts in pan and pour dressing over and place in oven.
Bake at 350°, turning several times.
Bake for 1 hour or until done.

title: bermuda salad bowl
directions: Wash cauliflower; separate into florets and cut in thin crosswise slices. Cut onion in crosswise slices and separate rings. Combine cauliflower, onion slices and French dressing. Chill. Wash lettuce; drain and shred. Toss with cheese and cauliflower mixture in salad bowl.

title: butter baked chicken and gravy
directions: Dip chicken in milk, then roll in mixture of flour, salt and pepper. Melt butter in baking dish. Put floured chicken in dish, skin side down, and bake uncovered in 400° to 425° oven for 30 minutes.

title: sally's french toast strata
directions: Cut French bread into cubes (about 12 cups).
Grease a 3-quart rectangular baking pan.
Place half of the bread cubes in the dish.
Top with cream cheese cubes and remaining bread cubes.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg.
Add sifted dry ingredients, alternately with milk.
Batter will be stiff. Carefully fold in blueberries.
Turn into greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan; sprinkle top with sugar.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes (325° for glass pan).
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Wash berries and drain.
Bake 2 pie shells.
Let cool, then line them with berries.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, water and syrup in a boiler.
Cook until thick, then add Jell-O to mixture.
Mix well and pour over strawberries.
Let cool if desired.
When ready to serve, put whipped cream over pie.

title: charlo's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef and season to taste.
Saute pepper and onions in butter. Combine all ingredients in saucepan and simmer over low heat for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Add 2 tablespoons flour to thicken.

title: old fashioned stew
directions: Brown beef in shortening in skillet.
Add 2 cups water. Simmer for 2 hours, or until tender.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer for 1 hour longer.
Thicken liquid for gravy if desired.

title: stephanie's lemon pie
directions: Mix milk and lemonade, then mix in Cool Whip.
Put in pie shell(s); chill.

title: pizza dip
directions: Press cream cheese in bottom of 9-inch pie pan.
Spread pizza sauce over this.
Layer remaining ingredients in order listed, except chips.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes, until hot and bubbly.
Serve with chips.

title: melting blueberry cake
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy, then add 1/4 cup of the sugar and beat until stiff.
Set aside.
Cream remaining sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks and beat until well blended.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour with salt and baking powder. Add alternately with milk, beating after each addition.
Coat blueberries with tablespoon of flour.
Fold in egg whites and then fold in blueberries.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Tear tortillas into strips and line bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Saute onions, then add soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes and peppers; cook over low heat until mixed well.
Layer in pan the cooked chicken, chestnuts and cheese.
Pour soup mixture over top, then top off with more cheese.
Cover and cook at 375° for 45 minutes or until hot.
This dish can be made the night before and put in refrigerator.
Can also use turkey.

title: lemon salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and add diced bananas, drained pineapple and marshmallows.
Stir and let set.

title: lemon extract cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs, beat well.
Add lemon extract.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to cream mixture. Add fruit and nuts.
Bake in loaf pan at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: sweet nothingspuppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips with oleo.
Combine melted mixture with peanut butter and cereal.

title: turkey curry
directions: Brown celery and onion in
butter.
Add
flour and curry. Stir. Add milk and broth.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add turkey. Cook another 10 minutes. Serve over rice with usual curry condiments.
Serves 4 to 6. Great for leftover turkey. Can be frozen.

title: fruit relish
directions: Chop into small pieces.
Cook slow until thick.
Put spices in a bag and cook along with mixture.
Makes 5 pints.

title: hot spiced cranberry tea
directions: Place cinnamon sticks, cloves and nutmeg in cheesecloth bag. Combine with cranberry juice, apple cider, brown sugar and lemon juice in saucepan; mix well.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Strain into cups.
Yield:
22 servings.

title: simply elegant steak and rice
directions: Cut steak into strips; brown meat in oil and add onions. Saute until tender.
Blend rest of ingredients together.
Pour over steak.
Simmer until tender, 1 hour at 350°.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: lemon pudding dessert
directions: In a bowl, cut butter into the flour until crumbly.
Press into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 22 minutes or until set.
Cool on a wire rack.
In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Fold in 1 cup whipped topping.
Spread over crust.
In a mixing bowl, beat milk and pudding on low speed for 2 minutes.
Carefully spread over the cream cheese layer.
Top with the remaining whipped topping. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Yield: 12 to 16 servings.

title: mexican turkey roll-ups
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine turkey, 1/2 cup sour cream, 1 1/2 teaspoons taco seasoning, 1/2 can soup, 1 cup cheese, onion, salsa and olives.
Place 1/3 cup filling on each tortilla.
Roll up and place, seam down, in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Combine remaining sour cream, taco seasoning and soup.
Pour over tortillas.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Serve with shredded lettuce and chopped tomatoes, if desired.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat, peppers and onion with salt.
Add garlic, cumin, chili mix and flour.
Cook 2 minutes.
Do not drain.
Add beans, tomato sauce and water.
Simmer slowly for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat; add soup and tomato sauce. Add spices and simmer 15 minutes.
Cook noodles; drain and rinse with cold water.
Place one-half the noodles in the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour one-half the meat sauce over the noodles and sprinkle with one-half the grated cheese.
Repeat layering remaining ingredients and sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 1 hour.

title: mocha cake
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add remaining items and beat smooth.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Do not open oven for at least 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and put in 2-quart buttered casserole.
Make topping.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine dates, soda and water; cool.
Combine butter, flour, soda, sugar and eggs, beating after each egg.
Add cocoa and salt. Add mixture to date mixture.
Combine nuts, sugar and chocolate chips, then sprinkle on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes enough to fill the two pie shells.
Refrigerate until use.
Will freeze and last for months.

title: wild rice and turkey casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Cover tightly; bake about 50 minutes or until rice is tender.
Uncover; bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: health bread(no sugar or eggs)
directions: Soak raisins for 5 minutes in boiling water; cool and drain. Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Add raisins last.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
May be kept in freezer.

title: noodle kugel
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Add butter to hot noodles to melt. Add other ingredients.
Reserve 1 tablespoon of cinnamon-sugar to put on top.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours in a 9 x 13-inch dish sprayed with Pam (or other nonstick product).
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of cinnamon-sugar on top.

title: brunch delight
directions: Cut eggs in half.
Mix together yolks, mayo, salt, curry, paprika and mustard.
Stuff eggs with mix.
Fill a 6 x 10-inch pan with eggs.
Mix remaining ingredients together ( except 1/4 cup cheese and 1 cup croutons).
Pour mix over eggs.
Top with croutons and remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour in pie crust.
Chill 3 hours, then top with strawberries and desired amount of glaze.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cinnamon together.
In unbaked pie shell, place layer of apples.
Sprinkle flour and sugar mix over apples. Alternate apples and flour until all is used.
Mix 1/2 cup butter and 1 cup brown sugar.
Drop on top of pie.
Strip pastry across pie.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: eggnog toast
directions: Dip bread into eggnog.
Cover both sides.
Cook in hot oil until golden, turning once.
Sift on powdered sugar.

title: gazpacho(low-fat antioxidants)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Cover.
Chill 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: pizza cups
directions: Spray muffin pans with cooking spray.
Press refrigerator biscuits in bottom and up sides.
Put on pizza sauce, other ingredients, then cheese.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: christmas strawberries
directions: Heat butter; add sugar, eggs and dates.
Cook until dates are melted.
Add flour; stir until thick.
Add nuts, cereal, salt and vanilla.
Cool mixture slightly.
Shape into strawberry shapes and roll in red sugar.
Dip the top in green sugar.

title: kraut salad
directions: Put sugar and vinegar in pan. Bring to boil. Pour over vegetables. Mix well. Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: rolled butter cookies
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together.
Cream butter.
Add egg and vanilla.
Stir with fork.
Add to flour mixture.
Roll on floured board and cut in desired shapes.	Bake at 350° for 9 to 10
minutes.

title: sweet sour pork chops
directions: Brown chops in oil.
Place in baking dish.
Combine all other ingredients except onion and green pepper in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Cook 2 minutes.
Pour thickened sauce over pork chops and top with onion and green pepper.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven 1 1/2 hours until chops are done.

title: peanut butter mounds
directions: Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Stir in marshmallows and Cracker Jacks.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Let set in refrigerator 4 hours or overnight.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: burrito supreme
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare meat according to package, browning meat; drain.
After draining, add onions and crushed tomatoes.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Drain excess liquids.
Fill each tortilla shell.
Roll and place in square baking pan sprayed with Pam.
Heat chilli in pan on top of stove.
Cover rolled tortillas with chilli; top with shredded cheese.
Heat in oven until cheese is melted.
Remove from oven.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes. Serve with sour cream and picante sauce.
Makes 4 to 8 servings. Enjoy.

title: garlic-studded pork loin with potatoes and carrots
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a small bowl, combine the pineapple concentrate, mustard, soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Peel the garlic and cut each clove lengthwise into thirds.
With a sharp knife, make 18 slits randomly in pork loin.
Tuck a piece of garlic into each slit.
Place the pork loin in a small roasting pan and brush the pork loin with half of the pineapple-mustard mixture.
Pour 1/2 cup chicken stock into the bottom of the pan.
Roast the pork loin 30 minutes.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Put all ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Store in a jar.
For 1 cup of hot spiced tea, put 2 teaspoons mixture in cup. Fill with boiling water and stir.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix instant pudding with 5 cups milk.
Line pan with graham crackers.
Put pudding over crackers.
Take Cool Whip and put over pudding.
Coat graham crackers with chocolate icing and put on top.
Refrigerate for 10 to 12 hours.

title: picante sauce
directions: Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer with lid on for 1 hour.

title: german apple pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place 2 round 8-inch cake pans in the oven.
Beat eggs, flour, milk and salt in small mixer bowl on medium speed 1 minute.
Remove the hot pans and place 2 tablespoons butter in each pan; rotate the pan until the butter coats insides.
Arrange 1/2 of the apples in the bottom of one cake pan and 1/2 in the bottom of another.
Divide the batter evenly and pour 1/2 into each pan.
Mix cinnamon and sugar; sprinkle on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Serve hot, cut into wedges.

title: clay dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix wet ingredients together. Blend both batches. Stir over low heat until it forms a ball. Knead a bit.
Cool.
Store in plastic container.
Enjoy!

title: old fashioned raisin bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all the ingredients, except bread and 1/2 cup of the sugar.
Place in a 2-quart square glass pan. Place this pan on a large 9 x 13-inch metal pan.
Fill the metal pan with hot water so that it comes up about to 1/2 the glass pan. Bake one hour or until knife comes out clear from center.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix ingredients and add enough mayonnaise to mix and stay together.
May make into more than 1 ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: barbecue hot dogs
directions: Cook onion in oil for 5 minutes.
Add all other ingredients and pour over hot dogs in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot on buns.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Soften or melt margarine. Add peanut butter and mix well. Then add graham crackers and powdered sugar. Mix well. Press into 9 x 13 pan.

title: lace cookies
directions: Pour oatmeal in bowl.
Pour oleo (melted) over oatmeal.
Stir. Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix with oatmeal mixture.
Beat egg and vanilla together.
Mix with oatmeal.
Cover cookie sheet with foil.
Drop cookies 1/2 teaspoon at a time.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Cool before removing from foil.
Chopped nuts may be added.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; season with salt and pepper. Spread in 11 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Cheddar cheese, then diced chiles over Cheddar, then Monterey Jack cheese over chiles. Combine milk, flour and eggs in a bowl and mix well with wire whisk.
Pour mixture over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Top with tomato sauce and bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain vegetables and mix with other ingredients (except almonds, butter and crackers).
Pour first ingredients in casserole dish.
Melt butter; add Ritz crackers and place on top of vegetables.
Sprinkle almonds on top of this.
Bake at 375° about 35 to 40 minutes or until set.

title: super pea salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients all together.
Mix the remaining ingredients well and pour over the first mixture.
Let set at least 4 hours before serving; overnight is better. Will keep, covered, at least 3 weeks.

title: key lime pie
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
With wire whisk, stir in yogurt and fold in Cool Whip.
Pour mixture into prepared crust.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 2 hours. (3 points or 148 calories per slice.)
This is good, too, made with strawberry jello.

title: marla's homemade apple pie
directions: Combine flour, salt and sugar. Cut the shortening into the mix until crumbly. Beat the egg; add water and vinegar and blend into the flour mixture until all of the flour is moist. Don't overbeat. Divide in half and place on wax paper. Keep cool until ready to roll out.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix butter cake mix, margarine and eggs and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar, eggs and vanilla and pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: luscious chocolate dessert
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Mix first three ingredients together and press into greased pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes. Let cool.

title: pimiento salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate. This is pretty served on lettuce.

title: parmesan oven-fried chicken
directions: Combine crumbs, cheese, almonds, parsley, salt and pepper in shallow bowl.
Melt butter with garlic powder in shallow baking dish.
Dip chicken pieces into butter; dip into crumb mixture. Place chicken, skin side up, in baking dish.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: vegetable cheese tart
directions: Cut off the stems and leaves from the beets.
Wash beets in running cold water.
Put them in a deep pan and cover with water. Add turmeric and bring to a boil.
Cook for 20 minutes or until they are fully cooked but still firm to the touch.
Let cool. Peel and rinse under running water.
Slice into 1/4-inch matchstick pieces.

title: crab bites
directions: Mix all ingredients except English muffins and spread on muffins (12 halves), refrigerate.
Before broiling, cut each muffin half into 6 pieces.
Broil for 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: file gumbo
directions: Fry together onions, scallions, garlic and pepper.
Place these fried vegetables with water, flour and Gravy Master in saucepan.
Fill halfway with water.

title: my little garden salad
directions: Let your child arrange the pieces of the cut-up carrot and apple on the lettuce leaf.
Top with yogurt and raisins.
Great for a snack or salad.

title: cheesy cheddar potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients, breaking up potatoes with spoon if necessary.
Spoon into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix
all ingredients and top with crushed potato chips. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: freezer pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt in large bowl.
With pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in shortening until mixture resembles cornmeal in texture.
Add water and mix lightly until the flour mixture absorbs the water and it resembles putty.
If dough is too sticky, add 1/4 cup flour more.
Divide dough into 10 oblong rolls.
Wrap well and freeze.
Makes enough for 10 double crust pies or 20 single.

title: orange cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix jello and cottage cheese.
Add fruit.
Stir in Cool Whip. Chill for several hours or overnight before serving.

title: beans delight
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add tomatoes and remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil; let simmer 20 minutes.
A quick hot meal perfect for those nights when the kids come home from soccer practice. Add hot tortillas or cornbread (the kind from a box, of course)!

title: apple fritters
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine egg, milk, apple, sugar, salt orange peel, juice and vanilla.
Stir together flour and baking powder; fold into egg mixture, stirring just until moistened.

title: green corn cakes
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients all together, beating hard.
Season with a little white pepper, salt and butter, stirring it well in and add a little flour to make the ingredients adhere together, being careful not to have them too thick.
Bake on the griddle first to test the batter, that it may be of the right consistency and well seasoned before baking to serve.
If preferred, fry in hot drippings or lard.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine and blend with wafer crumbs to make a crust.
Beat eggs, 2 sticks margarine and 10x sugar until light and fluffy (about 10 minutes).
Place on top of crust.
Slice bananas on top of this layer, then cover with crushed pineapple. Beat Dream Whip as directed on package, then fold in Cool Whip. Place on top of pineapple.
Sprinkle on chopped nuts.
Top with sliced strawberries.
Keep refrigerated overnight.

title: mushroom spread
directions: Cook bacon and crumble.
In drippings, saute onion and garlic. Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a slow boil; simmer until thickened, stirring constantly.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: With mixer beat in enough flour until thick.
With spoon, add enough flour for a stiff dough.
(Use Pillsbury flour for easier rolling.)
Divide dough in small enough pieces to roll easy.
Roll out each piece as thin as possible.
Place on cloth until dough is partially dry.
Roll as jelly roll and cut very fine.
Cook chicken until tender, remove from bone and cut in pieces.
Add noodles to boiling broth; cook until tender.
Add chicken last.

title: split pea soup
directions: Soak peas overnight.
Combine peas, celery, onions, carrots and ham.
Cover ingredients with water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat.
Cover with lid and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Water may be added if soup becomes too thick.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Prepare 1 box of brownies as directed using 4 eggs.
Spread in greased pan.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, egg and flour in same bowl until well blended.
Spoon mixture over brownie batter and swirl with a knife.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: bill's citrus marmalade
directions: Slice fruit thin.
Add 2 cups for each cup of fruit.
Let soak for 24 hours.
After 24 hours boil for 30 minutes, let stand 24 hours.
Mix 1 cup sugar to each cup of fruit.
Boil approximately 20 minutes or until jelled.

title: potato salad
directions: Add and mix egg, sugar, flour, vinegar and water (add vinegar and water last).
Cook together until it thickens.
This is over medium heat.
Add to this the butter, mayonnaise, and mustard. Add to this the potatoes, onions, celery, salt and pepper to taste.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Grease 9-inch pie pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine and beat at medium speed flour, baking powder, salt, pudding, margarine, egg and milk.
Pour into pie pan.
Place drained peaches evenly on batter.
Combine and beat for 2 minutes cream cheese, sugar and peach juice.
Spread over peaches about 1 inch from edge.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar on top.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: quesadilla
directions: A quick, semi-sweet cake good with milk, tea or coffee.

title: cinnamon twists
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Separate buscuits.
Roll buscuits into 6-inch rolls.
Dip biscuits in butter.
Mix cinnamon and sugar in a bowl.
Roll biscuits in cinnamon and sugar.
Twist the biscuits. Cook for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hummus
directions: In a small bowl, combine tahini, cumin, salt and garlic.
While stirring, slowly pour in lemon juice, then hot water.

title: prickly pear jelly
directions: Despine
the
fruit
leaving
as much skin as possible. Cut fruit
into quarters and include the seeds.
Place in a 4 or
6 quart vessel and add water.
Boil over medium heat until fruit is soft, about 30 minutes.

title: country potato soup
directions: In large saucepan combine potatoes, celery, onions, water, bouillon and salt.
Cover and cook until vegetables are tender (about 20 min.)
Don't over cook potatoes; they should be just tender, not mushy.
Add 1 cup milk and heat.

title: wassail(hot)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large saucepan. Tie spices in a cheesecloth bag. Add to cider and boil 20 minutes. Serve in mug with cinnamon stick.
Makes 8 servings.

title: almond chicken salad
directions: Combine all but last 3 ingredients.
Toss lightly.
Mix vinegar, salt and mayonnaise.
Add to chicken mixture.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tomato juice
directions: Put tomatoes through sieve.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bring to a boil and can.
I can all my tomato juice this way.
It's a lot better to use in stuff than plain juice.

title: blueberry nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease well and flour lightly one 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or two 4 x 6 x 3-inch pans. Sprinkle berries (frozen) with small amount of flour and sugar and toss lightly. Set aside. Sift and combine all dry ingredients, except sugar, in large bowl. In small bowl, beat eggs and sugar together; add milk and butter. Make a well in dry ingredients and pour liquid into it. Combine with a few strokes, just enough to moisten everything. Lightly fold in blueberries and nuts. Fill pans about 1/2 full. Bake in 350° oven for an hour. Test with skewer. If tester does not come clean, bake for 10 minutes more or until golden brown. Cool on rack for 5 to 7 minutes before removing from pan.

title: crystallized violets
directions: Remove violet heads from stalks.
Wash very carefully and pat dry with paper towel.
Put sugar and water into saucepan over medium heat and bring to boil.
Heat until syrup reaches 240°F/120°C on thermometer.
Continue to boil for one minute. Reduce heat and drop in flowers, a few at a time.
Leave to simmer for one minute.
Remove carefully with slotted spoon.
Drain well and place on a sheet of foil to cool.
Turn at least once.
Store in airtight tin.

title: maple syrup
directions: In saucepan, heat the sugar and water until mixture boils. Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat and stir in maple flavoring. If desired, add butter.
Makes 1 1/4 cups syrup.

title: hamburg and sausage soup
directions: In large kettle, brown hamburg and sausage.
Drain well.
Add seasonings, herbs and soup mix.
Stir in boiling water, tomato juice and soy sauce.
Add raw vegetables and macaroni; stir well. Cover and bring to boil; turn to simmer for 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
May also be cooked in a crock-pot for 8 hours on low temperature, 4 to 5 hours on high.
Serves 6 or more.

title: jack frost
directions: Combine Jack Daniels whiskey, Drambuie, cherry juice, orange juice and sweet and sour mix over ice in tall glass.
Garnish with a cherry.

title: company chicken roll-ups with noodles
directions: Remove loose center portion of chicken breasts (save and use for stir-fry).
Lightly salt and pepper breasts.
Divide asparagus among chicken breasts and roll up.
Wrap each breast with a slice of bacon.
Dilute soup and pour over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes (until chicken is done).

title: bangers n' mash
directions: Cook in a skillet the sausage links.
Serve with mashed potatoes and baked beans.
Pour gravy over potatoes and sausage. You can make your own gravy or use the packets.
The more gravy, the better!
Can also use ketchup.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts in the bottom of the pan.
Make the chocolate cake mix according to the directions.
Pour the mix on top of the coconut layer.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and butter.
Add vanilla.
Drop this by spoonfuls over unbaked cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: all italian meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine ground beef, eggs, bread crumbs, Spatini mix and catsup.

title: saucy pork chops
directions: Season chops.
Flour and brown in skillet.
Place chops in dish to serve and place rest of ingredients over chops and lay pineapple on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: reese's peanut butter bars
directions: Thoroughly mix peanut butter, butter, sugar and cracker crumbs.
Press hard into baking sheet with sides until even and firmly packed.
Spread melted chocolate chips over top.
Cut into small squares, approximately 50.
Refrigerate overnight or freeze for 1 hour before removing from pan.
Rich and delicious!

title: aunt catherine's unbelievable cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and roll into balls.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten by crisscrossing with a fork. Bake at 350° for about 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: barbecue party franks
directions: Cut each wiener into 5 pieces.
These will "puff up" after marinating and heating.

title: lemon strawberry angel cream cake
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water for 5 minutes.
Beat egg yolks and 3/4 cup sugar until light and creamy.
Add lemon juice and continue beating.
Cook this mixture in double boiler until it thickens slightly.
Add softened gelatin.
Cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff and slowly add 1/2 cup sugar as beating continues.
Fold cooled yolk mixture into whites.
Remove brown crust from cake, then pull cake apart in 1-inch pieces.
Fold cake into egg mixture. Place in medium size pan.
Chill in refrigerator.
Cover with whipped cream and sprinkle with coconut.
Top with strawberries.

title: chocolatetown pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients with mixer.
Stir in pecans and chocolate chips.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes to an hour.

title: chicken broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Brown onion in margarine.
Add Cheez Whiz and soup.
Stir well until smooth.
Mix broccoli, rice and meat.
Stir in cheese mixture.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350° in 2-quart casserole dish or 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: beef chowder
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Spoon off grease.
Add tomatoes, 4 cups hot water, bouillon cubes, salt, pepper, bay leaf, celery and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 30 minutes. Add noodles, mixed vegetables and thyme.
Return to boil and cook 15 minutes longer.

title: ham sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a small bowl.
Score ham. Pour 1/2 mixture on ham.
Approximately 20 minutes before ham is done; pour on other 1/2 of mixture.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Wash zucchini; slice thin.
Slice onion thin.
Add to zucchini.
Add salt.
Cover with water.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain through. Bring remaining ingredients to boiling.
Pour over zucchini and onion.
Let stand 2 hours.
Bring all ingredients to boiling point and heat 5 minutes.
Put in jars and bath off.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Toss with dressing of your choice. Serves 6.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Crumble corn bread.
Mix mayonnaise and pickle juice and pour over all vegetables; stir.
Layer bread and vegetables.
Crumble crisp bacon on top.

title: easy cheesy asparagus bake
directions: Drain asparagus.
Reserve a few pieces for garnish.
Place remaining asparagus in an 8-inch shallow baking dish with red pepper.
Combine mayonnaise, cheese and onion.
Fold in egg white. Spread over asparagus.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake 1 hour at 275°.

title: ooee goee cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spread into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (greased).

title: slow cooker chops
directions: Brown chops and remove from pan. Combine remaining ingredients and heat in pan in which chops were browned.
Layer chops and sauce in slow cooker or heavy Dutch oven.
Either bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour or in slow cooker on high setting until bubbly, then simmer on low until tender and sauce is consistency of gravy, 5 or 6 hours.

title: chess pies
directions: Cream sugar, butter, egg yolks and vanilla. Add raisins and nuts. Mix well. Line muffin pans with pie crusts and then add 1 heaping tablespoon of filling to each pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. After baked, add meringue and brown in oven. Makes 1 doz.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Break up broccoli and cauliflower into large bowl.
Mix together bacon bits, salad dressing and enough milk so it is creamy.
Add to broccoli mixture.
Top with grated cheese.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Cream butter in large bowl at high speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Gradually add sugar.
Continue beating at high speed until light and fluffy.
By hand, stir in flour, frosting mix and walnuts until well blended.
Pour batter into 10-inch greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes. Cool 2 hours.
Remove from pan.
Does not need icing, may pour over top with fruit pie filling.

title: fiesta dip
directions: Divide onion; half will be for garnish and half for the avocados.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Cook 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mushroom meat balls
directions: Roll out meat balls to desired size.
Cook meat balls until done; drain grease.
Mix together mushroom soup and cream of onion soup with 1 can of water.
Pour over meat balls.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: candied apples with red hots
directions: Put in skillet and cook.
Add red cake coloring.

title: fruit fizz
directions: Mix apricot nectar, pineapple juice and orange juice in a large pitcher.
Chill well.
Just before serving, add 1 1/2 cups icy cold ginger ale.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream cheese, butter, and margarine until light and fluffy. Gradually add sugar (half cup at a time).
Add eggs one at a time and mix well after each addition.
Add cake flour (half cup at a time) and mix well each time until all flour is added.
Stir in lemon flavoring.
Pour in bundt pan and bake at 350° for one hour and 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in cake comes out clean.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Season to your taste (chili powder). Add beans, soup and tomatoes.
Simmer.
Pour chips into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour meat mixture on top.
Cover top with cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: ada polo ba gusht
directions: Boil lentils in enough salted water until tender, but not soft.
Drain and set aside.
Rinse the rice several times in warm water; soak in warm water and set aside.
Bring a large pot of salty (2 tablespoons) water to a rapid boil.
Drain the water from the soaked rice; pour the rice in boiling water.
Boil 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally to prevent the grains from sticking together.
Drain the rice in a colander; rinse cold tap water over rice.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook in a 2-quart casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: snowy pecans
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together in a lunch size paper sack. Roast pecans in butter in microwave about 3 minutes. Add to paper sack and shake real good. Pour on paper towel. Then store in airtight container.

title: tropical chicken salad
directions: *May want to start out with 1/4 cup mayonnaise and add up to 1/2 cup if needed.

title: e z overnite casserole
directions: Stir all together and place in refrigerator overnite -covered in a 9 x 13 baking pan.
Bake uncovered in 350 oven for 1 hour. Great way to use left over ham, chicken or turkey.

title: jumping jambalaya
directions: In a large wok, melt butter.
Add shrimp and when nearly done, add drained okra, salt, pepper and garlic.
Add water, rice, Texas Pete hot sauce and pepper flakes.
Simmer until rice is done.
Add stewed tomatoes by tossing or blending.
Let stand for 30 minutes. A great leftover.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Put in one loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: apple crisp(microwave)
directions: Place apples in square dish (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix remaining ingredients with fork until crumbly and sprinkle over apples.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Put sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in a skillet and bring to a boil; let boil for 1 minute.
Add this mixture to all other ingredients.
Dip cookies onto wax paper to cool.

title: microwave coconut pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and mix well.
Cook 2 minutes at 80% in microwave.
Stir; cook 2 more minutes.
Stir and cook 2 more minutes.
Mix egg yolks with small amount of cooked mixture and cook 2 more minutes.
Stir in margarine, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into crust; top with meringue and coconut.
Brown top.

title: holiday cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin with boiling water.
Add cold water and pineapple juice.
Chill.
When the gelatin is practically congealed, add the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into a Bundt pan lightly rubbed with mayonnaise.
Chill until firm.
Turn out.

title: melissa's overnight spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti into smaller pieces and cook according to directions on package.
Drain and rinse under cold water; drain well.
Mix all ingredients and moisten well with a good brand of Italian oil and vinegar dressing.
Let stand overnight.
Keeps well if there is any left.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in a little water until tender.
Fry onion in margarine until clear.
Drain squash and mix with onion.
Add 1 cup cracker crumbs or stuffing mix, 1 cup cheese and soup. Pour into baking dish. Top with rest of crumbs and cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: sour beef and dumplings(pressure cooker method)
directions: Place cloves, allspice and bay leaf in a spice ball or spice ball made with cheese cloth.

title: breaded venison
directions: Pound your venison down very thin, dip in egg mixture then in bread crumbs.
Fry in a small amount of oil about 3 minutes on each side.
Enjoy!

title: window glass jello salad
directions: Separately prepare orange, lime and cherry jello with 1 1/2 cups water for each flavor.
Put each prepared jello in 9-inch pan and jell overnight.
Prepare lemon jello in 1 cup water.
Add sugar and pineapple juice.
Let set awhile in refrigerator, but do not jell all the way.
Beat lemon jello mixture until lemony colored.

title: clam dip
directions: Blend all ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve with potato chips or crackers.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: In a large skillet, saute onions, celery and carrots in margarine for 5 minutes.
Add the next 5 ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Place mixture in an oblong or 2-quart casserole dish and cover with mashed potatoes.
Sprinkle with paprika and grated cheese.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: easy stroganoff
directions: Mix onion soup mix, sour cream and mushroom soup together. Brown steak in skillet.
Pour mixture over steak.
Bake in 350° oven
for 1 hour or so.
Serve over hot noodles.

title: rainbow poke cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Bake as directed. Cool for 10 minutes.
Spoon raspberry over 1 layer.
Repeat with lime gelatin.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: Beat egg whites and add cream of tartar.
Blend cottage cheese in blender until smooth.
Whip egg yolks and add to cottage cheese mixture.
Fold into egg whites.
Pour into skillet as you would pancakes and bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: overnight egg bake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Butter each slice bread and cut in 6 slices each.
Put half bread in bottom of pan; cover with half of cheese.
Top with other half bread and cheese.
Mix other ingredients; pour over bread and cheese.
Puncture bread with fork several times to soak up mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: jello cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Make Jell-O with 3/4 cup boiling water and 3/4 cup cold water; dissolve and pour over cake.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Bake at 400°. Makes 5 dozen.

title: onion pie
directions: Use enough finely sliced onions to fill the pie shell.
Place in boil.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand 15 minutes.
Drain and place in pie shell.
Sprinkle flour over onions and add cream. Stir gently with fork and then dot with butter.
Sprinkle with pepper and bake at 400° until nice and brown (about 45 minutes). Serve warm.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Brown chuck.
Add onion.
Simmer until onion is tender.
Drain grease.
Add mushroom soup, sour cream and milk.
Stir.
Let simmer.
Add more milk as needed to keep gravy thinned and prevent sticking. Stir cooked and drained noodles into meat mixture.
When heating from leftovers, always add more milk.

title: can't wait apple cake
directions: Mix apples, oil and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Mix together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon; add to batter using spoon.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Batter will be stiff.
Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: italian chicken
directions: Combine salad dressing, lemon juice, bouillon and pepper. Place chicken in baking dish and pour liquid on top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken curry
directions: Pressure cook chicken or crock-pot off bone.
Combine all ingredients and bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar, then let stand.
Dissolve jello in warm water.
Chill until partially set, then add celery, orange and pecans.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: lemon refrigerator cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and beat until smooth.
Beat in lemon juice and lemon peel.
Stir in flour and salt.
Divide dough in half and place on a large square of waxed paper.
Knead lightly to blend thoroughly.
Shape each half into a roll about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Wrap rolls in waxed paper, twisting ends of rolls closed.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours (dough can kept up to 1 week in refrigerator).

title: vinegar pie
directions: Melt margarine, then mix all together and put into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for ten minutes, then reduce to 300°.
Bake until brown.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Stir ingredients until smooth.
Add Cool Whip; stir to blend. Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts and freeze.
Remove from freezer about 15 minutes before serving.

title: quick and easy lasagna
directions: Mix in saucepan the tomato paste, water, oregano, pepper and salt; cook on low around 15 minutes.
While sauce cooks, brown ground beef; drain off fat.
Add Italian seasoning, sugar and sauce.
Boil noodles until tender.

title: mediterranean medley salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except salad greens.
Cover tightly and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Serve over salad greens. I never use the radishes, bell peppers and tomatoes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat together and chill.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: chocolate banana pudding pie
directions: Pour into a large bowl.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat with a wire whisk 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Spoon over bananas in crust.
Spread with whipped topping.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients to 280°.
Sample dropped in water will be hard.
Add 2 cups peanuts; cook about 3 minutes, until light golden brown.
Add soda.
Remove at once from heat; add vanilla and butter as soon as foaming has subsided, pour into greased shallow pan.
When cool, break into pieces.
Foolproof if you use candy thermometer.

title: butterscotch-peanut butter pie
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan, combine pudding mix and gelatin; add milk and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Add peanut butter and let cool to room temperature.
Spread pudding mixture over prepared crust.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Spread top with Cool Whip.

title: adventure cookies
directions: Boil butter and sugar.
Add dates; boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from fire and add eggs, salt and milk.
Return to fire and cook 2 more minutes.
Remove from fire and cool, then add remainder of ingredients.
Let set 1/2 hour, then roll into balls and roll in chopped coconut.
Keep cool.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs, sugar and oil until well mixed.
Mix together flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon. Add to sugar-egg mixture
together with zucchini.
Add walnuts, raisins and vanilla.
Bake in 350° oven in greased and floured pan for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: grits and cheese
directions: Cook grits, water and salt in large heavy saucepan.
Cook on top of stove for 5 minutes, stirring often.
Remove from stove and stir in cheese and butter.	Beat eggs into milk and add to grit mixture.
Buttered bread crumbs may be added on top if you care for them.
Bake about 45 minutes at 325°.
A deep dish is good for baking.
Jalapeno cheese can be used if you like the hot flavor instead of the garlic.

title: cherry or blueberry delight
directions: Layer cherry pie filing, pineapple, dry cake mix and nuts. Combine 1 melted stick margarine and 2 tablespoons pineapple juice.
Pour evenly over above.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: assorted bean soup
directions: Put all but potato in pot of cold water; cook on low heat for 4 hours.
Add potato and cook until potato is done.

title: one pan meal
directions: Mix together the ground beef and seasonings; cook and drain. Mix the onion and green pepper together.
Layer in a large pan: the meat, onion and green pepper, potatoes, cheese and spaghetti sauce.
End with sauce on top.
Bake, covered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked beans
directions: In a skillet, brown ground meat, salt, pepper and onion. After browning, strain out fat.
Pour beans and ketchup into casserole dish; add ground meat.
Stir and add brown sugar; mix well.
Bake in a 350° (preheated) oven for 2 1/2 hours, stirring every 1/2 hour.

title: easy chili
directions: Pour tomatoes in colander over chili pot.
Cut tomatoes in small pieces.
Brown beef and chopped onion together; add other ingredients.
Simmer until done, about 30 minutes.
Pass grated cheese and chopped onions for topping.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook hamburger.
Drain and crumble.
Add taco sauce; mix and cool.
Cut up lettuce.
Add onion, green pepper, tomatoes and cheese.
To serve, toss all together with dressing.
Squish taco chips and garnish top of salad.

title: saucy twist pork dish
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.
In large skillet, cook and stir onion and green pepper in butter until onion is tender.
Stir in macaroni and remaining ingredients.
Pour into ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover; bake for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs; place in greased casserole.
Top with bread crumbs last ten minutes of baking. Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Yields 6 servings.

title: bacon, ham, mushroom quiche
directions: Mix together.
Pour into deep pie shell.
Bake at 375° until top is lightly brown and firm.

title: beef roll-ups
directions: Soften cream cheese; spread on dried beef.
Quarter whole sweet pickles and lay on one side of dried beef.
Roll up.
Put a toothpick through the roll and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.

title: citrus tea
directions: Combine 2 cups water and cloves in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Remove from heat and let stand 2 hours.
Bring 1 1/2 quarts water to boil in large saucepan.
Add tea bags.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Strain clove mixture and add to tea.
Add fruit juices and sugar.
Stir well and let stand 1 hour. Warm over low heat and serve.
Great for holidays and cold winter days.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix well and roll in pecans.
Better if it sits 2 days.

title: beer cheese spread
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler until blended.
Gradually beat in remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook until all ingredients have blended, stirring twice.
Serve hot or cold with fresh French bread, torn, or vegetables.

title: my hush puppies
directions: Mix together and drop into hot grease while frying fish.

title: chicken and mushrooms
directions: Wash and skin chicken breasts; drain and place in a lightly buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Slice and saute fresh mushrooms in margarine. Add cream of mushroom soup.
Heat and pour over chicken.
Cover and cook at 350° for about 1 hour or until chicken is tender.

title: cottage cheese jello salad
directions: Jell jello's slightly.
Mix all and chill.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain and rinse well the sauerkraut.
Add sugar, oil, vinegar, pimentos, chopped onion and chopped celery.
Mix well and keep refrigerated.
Stir occasionally.
Gets better with age, about 3 to 7 days.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, sour cream, cream of chicken soup, onions, some of the Cheddar and Velveeta cheeses, saving enough to cover mixture.
Cover with Grape-Nuts and drizzle the rest of margarine over completed mixture.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: grilled fish and vegetables
directions: Dip each fish fillet in melted butter and sprinkle Old Bay seasoning well on each side, patting it by hand and do the same with bread crumbs.
Cook on very hot grill in flames for 2 minutes on each side.
Lower the fire and then cook vegetables.
Serve grilled fish with grilled vegetables on the side.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients.
Better if mixed at least 1 day before serving to blend flavors.

title: uncooked oatmeal cookies
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients in a pot and boil for 1 minute. Remove from fire. Add nuts and oatmeal and stir. Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet. Let cool.

title: crunchy spinach salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine spinach, bean sprouts, water chestnuts, eggs, bacon and onion.
In a bottle or jar, combine all remaining ingredients.
Cover and shake well to mix.
Just before serving, pour dressing over salad and toss.
Serves 8.

title: berries preserved
directions: Bring to a boil and cook 10 minutes in a rolling boil, stirring constantly.

title: butter cookie("christmas cut-out cookies")
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Mix together the baking powder, egg yolks and flour.
Add to cream mixture and form into a ball.
Roll up and use cookie cutters to cut out cookies.
These can be decorated.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: peanut butter hash
directions: Using a piece of aluminum foil twice the size of an 8 x 8-inch baking pan, line pan with half the foil and cover candy with the other half.
Cover bottom of foil-lined pan with marshmallows. Melt butter over medium heat; add peanut butter and chocolate bits; stir until chocolate melts.
Remove from heat; stir in pecans and vanilla and pour over marshmallows.
Fold foil over candy and refrigerate until firm.
Peel off foil and cut candy into squares.

title: 24 hour roast
directions: Place all ingredients, except potatoes and carrots, in a large crock-pot.
Cook at 250° for at least 24 hours.
During the last 2 1/2 hours, add potatoes, peeled and quartered, and carrots, peeled and halved.
Serves approximately 6 people.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Put all together in a bowl and stir until well blended.
Do not use mixer.
Pour into well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
As soon as cake is done, punch cake full of holes.
Pour icing over cake while hot.

title: copper carrot pennies
directions: Cook carrots until almost tender. Cool carrots and slice. Cut up pepper and onion. Mix these 3 items. Mix remaining ingredients until well blended. Pour over vegetables and refrigerate overnight.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spoon pie filling evenly into bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Spread pineapple over cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pineapple.
Pour margarine evenly over all. Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Bake for 1 hour or until cake is done.
