title: raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins in 1 1/2 cups boiling water until tender; mix and sift flour and sugar and add slowly to raisins, stirring until thickened.
Add lemon rind and juice and nuts.
Cool; line pie pan with pastry.
Turn in mixture.
Top with a layer of pastry.
Wet edges of pastry.
Press together and trim.
Gash top to let steam escape.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat and bake 20 minutes longer at 325°.
Can omit grated rind of lemon and omit nuts.
I like to add 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon.

title: mouse's goulash
directions: Brown hamburger and add onions.
Combine the mustard, salt and paprika in a bowl.
Add the Worcestershire sauce, vinegar and ketchup to dry mixture.
Mix well.
Add ketchup mixture to meat. Add water.
Simmer over low heat about 20 minutes to half hour. Boil noodles until tender and add to meat mixture.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Serve.

title: golden crowned cauliflower
directions: Steam cauliflower in a small amount of water until tender-crisp.
Combine mayonnaise and mustard.
Spread over drained cauliflower which has been placed in glass baking dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until cheese melts and topping "puffs" slightly.
Yields 6 servings; contains 100 calories per serving.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown ground beef; drain and then rinse
in hot water.
In medium saucepan, melt cheese over very low heat.
Add ground beef, taco seasoning mix and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
To keep warm, pour dip into small crock-pot.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Mix sugar, butter and cream (milk).
Boil for 2 1/2 minutes. Remove and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until creamy. Spread on cake.

title: tuna walnut salad
directions: In bowl, combine tuna, onions, dressing and walnuts.
Cover; refrigerate until serving time, at least 4 hours.
Serve with slivers of carrots and red pepper, if desired.

title: dirt pudding
directions: You will also need 2 (6-inch) flowerpots lined with foil.

title: cheese potato soup
directions: Cook celery, potatoes and onion in broth.
Using blender, alternate soup, cheese and oleo.
Put small amounts in blender each time.
Pour into large pot to heat.
Can be frozen.

title: corn bread
directions: Blend all ingredients, stirring until well mixed.
Pour into 8 or 10-inch heavy skillet (well-greased).
Bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Put chopped rhubarb in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle Jell-O over rhubarb, then sprinkle sugar over all.
Then sprinkle yellow cake mix over all.
Pour melted oleo over, then pour water over everything.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease Bundt pan.
Mix cake as directed except reduce water by 1/4 cup.
Stir in nuts and curd.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool in pan for 25 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Grate lemon peel and squeeze juice from lemon. In a small bowl, mix powdered sugar with 4 1/2 teaspoons lemon juice.
(Glaze should be an easy spreading consistency, but not too runny.)
Spoon on cake.
Garnish with grated peel.

title: sweet and sour marinated steaks
directions: Place steaks in shallow dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and stir well.
Pour over steaks.
Cover and marinate for 4 hours in the fridge, turning occasionally.
Remove from marination and grill about 5 inches from hot coals until desired doneness.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan or 2 disposable aluminum loaf pans (Pam works well).
Mix all dry ingredients and raisins. Add butter and eggs.
Add buttermilk.
Mix with wooden spoon until dough is fluffy and wet.
Bake 1 large loaf for 1 hour and 20 minutes, or bake 2 smaller loaves 60 to 65 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Turn out on a rack to cool.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add mandarin oranges with juice and orange sherbet.
Stir until sherbet dissolves.
Pour into pan and refrigerate to set.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Put apples in an 8-inch square pan. Combine the rest of the ingredients, mixing until crumbly. Regular or instant oatmeal may be used.
Sprinkle on top of apples.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes, until apples are tender. Serves 6.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Place chicken pieces in bottom of 9 x 13 casserole dish. Mix soup and water, pour over chicken. Sprinkle with dressing mix. Pour broth over all. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: peach cantaloupe conserve ice cream topping
directions: Peel and dice peaches and cantaloupe.
Combine all ingredients except nut meats.
Cook mixture until thick and clear.
Add nut meats and pour into sterilized jars to within 1/2-inch of top.
Put cap; screw bands tight.
Process in boiling water bath 10 minutes. Yield:
6 to 8 oz. jars.

title: tody's dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling and pineapple in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish prepared with nonstick vegetable spray.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly on fruit; do not mix.
Place margarine slices on cake mix. Bake at 350° for 48 to 53 minutes.

title: oven grilled reubens
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix together sauerkraut & caraway seeds. Spread dressing on one side of each slice of read.
To 6 slices add corned beef.
Top other 6 slices of bread (dressing side down). Coat a baking sheet with cooking spray & and arrange sandwiches on sheet.
Coat a second baking sheet with spray and place coated side down on sandwiches and press lightly.
Bake 15-20 minutes or until golden.
Check after 10 minutes.
Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together with an electric beater. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Test after 30 minutes.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Heat water, vinegar and salt to boil.
Fill pint jar with cucumbers.
Add garlic, mustard seed, pepper and dill to each jar. Place lid and ring on jar and place in boiling water for 5 minutes to seal.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Add flour, sifted with baking powder (1 spoonful at a time), alternately with milk.
Add vanilla; stir in crushed pineapple and juice; blend well.
Pour batter into well-greased (spray) 10-inch tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Turn to 325° and bake for 1 1/2 hours or until top springs back when lightly touched.
Let stand in pan a few minutes. Remove to rack.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in 1/2-cup boiling water and set aside to cool. Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Add chocolate and vanilla. Mix together flour and soda. Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk. Mix only until flour is blended. Do not overmix. Stir in pecans and coconut. Pour into 4 greased and floured 9-inch pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake test is done.

title: baked stuffed shrimp(never fails to please)
directions: Lay butterflied shrimp in baking pan.
In a large bowl, combine the remaining ingredients to form stuffing mixture. Stuff each shrimp with a large spoonful of stuffing mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
(If desired, tops may be browned by broiling for 2 to 3 minutes.)

title: corn-celery casserole
directions: Combine corn (thaw slightly if needed), celery soup, salt and the pimento in a 2-quart casserole. Cover and bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: tarragon turkey dijon sandwich
directions: In a small bowl, blend cottage cheese, mustard and tarragon. Place lettuce leaf on one slice of bread and spread cottage cheese mixture over lettuce.
Place turkey on top; season lightly with salt and pepper.
Top with bell pepper strips and remaining slice of bread.
Makes one serving.

title: chocolate applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix flour, soda, cinnamon, allspice, cocoa, salt and cloves. Add alternately with applesauce in shortening and sugar mixture. Add raisins and nuts.
Bake in oblong pan at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: jello pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, melted butter and sugar.
Bake for 8 minutes at 400° in a 10 x 14-inch pan.
Cool.
Separately mix cream cheese and cup of sugar.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Put creamed mixture over pretzel mix.
Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Cool.
Add thawed strawberries to Jell-O and pour over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate until set.
Interesting taste.

title: crock-pot chicken and sauce
directions: Mix together, cream of mushroom soup, sour cream and cooking sherry in a crock-pot.
Put
in chicken breasts and then cover the chicken with sauce.
Add a pinch of salt and pepper (to taste). Cook on low all day or on high half day (4 to 5 hours). May serve over cooked egg noodles.

title: amish cookies
directions: Cream eggs, sugar, margarine, baking powder, soda and vanilla. Alternate flour and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown ground beef in oil. Add onion and brown some more.
Add tomato, celery, basil, garlic and lentils. Lastly, add cauliflower and potatoes. Add water and slow cook until the vegetables are cooked.

title: bubble bread
directions: Scald and cool the milk, shortening and sugar.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add eggs, then work in flour and salt. Let rise until double in bulk.
Knead down; let stand 10 minutes. Break off dough in balls about the size of walnuts.
Dip in a mixture of the sugar, cinnamon and butter (melted).
Drop in angel food pan; let rise.
Bake at 350° for 40 or 50 minutes.
Let cool in pan.

title: gonzales seafood gumbo
directions: Brown flour in cooking oil until rich brown, then add chopped onion and cook slowly until golden.
Add water, salt, pepper and green onions.
Bring to a boil.
When mixture boils, add shrimp and crab (if frozen or fresh).
Cook until shrimp are done.
At this point the mixture can be frozen, if desired.
When ready to serve, reheat to a boil and add oysters.
Cook 1 minute at a boil, or more if preferred.
Remove from heat and add file to taste (usually about 2 tablespoons).
Add parsley to garnish at this time.
Also liquid crab boil (1 drop or two) to give rich seafood flavor.

title: robin's enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; season with salt and pepper.
In a large pot, combine balance of ingredients and simmer approximately 30 to 35 minutes.
Soft-fry tortillas in oil; lay on paper towels to soak up some of the oil.
Roll tortilla in more tomato sauce that has been poured into pie plate.
Fill with meat mixture and roll up.
Cover enchiladas with grated cheese and bake at 375° until cheese is melted.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: In large heavy skillet or Dutch oven, cover chicken with water; add onion, celery salt, pepper and salt to taste.
Boil slowly, until tender.
Remove chicken from broth (save broth). Remove meat from bones; set aside.
Combine flour, 1 teaspoon salt and baking powder in bowl; cut in shortening.
Stir in milk with fork.
Turn onto lightly floured surface; roll very thin, cut into strips.
Add chicken to broth, bring to boil.
Drop in dumplings letting each layer cook for 5 minutes before adding another; cover.
Cook for at least 30 minutes or until done.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan or Dutch oven, melt butter.
Saute okra and garlic until tender.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Drain liquid from clams and keep clams in covered container in refrigerator.
Add clam liquid, water, tomatoes, tomato paste, barley, salt, Worcestershire sauce, red pepper sauce and cayenne to saucepan.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer over low heat for abou 1 hour or until barley is tender.
Just before serving, add clams, shrimp and crabmeat.
Simmer just until shrimp become opaque.
Do not overcook.

title: chex party mix
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter or margarine on a cookie sheet at 350°. While this is melting, mix in large bowl each cereal, peanuts, pretzels and cheese crackers.
When margarine is melted, remove from oven.
Add Worcestershire sauce to melted shortening and stir together.
Add contents of dry mixture to cover liquid.
Mix together so that all the dry ingredients become coated.
Sprinkle with the seasoning salt and mix again.
Heat in oven approximately 20 minutes.
Allow to cool before serving.
Repeat steps until all dry ingredients are used.
Use more or less of each ingredient, according to likes or dislikes.

title: fiesta luncheon
directions: Cook and drain macaroni. Saute sausage, onion and green pepper in skillet until sausage is done. Drain. Combine sausage mixture and the rest of ingredients except cheese. Pour into casserole dish, sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Make 3 holes. In one hole, put vinegar; in another, place oil and in the last, put in the vanilla.
Pour cold water over all and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top or fruit as desired.

title: best ever biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Thaw shrimp according to package directions.
Rinse and drain.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Spread cream cheese in a 6-inch dish or plate.
Combine sour cream, 1/2 cup cocktail sauce, hot pepper sauce in a small bowl.
Layer on top of cream cheese. Combine shrimp, remaining 1/4 cup cocktail sauce and parsley in another small bowl.
Layer shrimp mixture over sour cream mixture. Serve immediately.
House crackers.
Makes 3 cups.

title: crispy corn dog
directions: Mix flour, meal, sugar, mustard, milk and egg.
Put in glass. Dip wieners, 1 at a time and fry in hot cooking oil.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Boil the sugar and water until sugar is dissolved. Remove from heat and stir in lemonade and orange juice. Add bananas, grapes, pineapple and fruit cocktail.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mash avocados and mix with lemon juice.
Set aside.
Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix.
Set aside.
Layer each of the following in a large casserole dish and refrigerate:
bean dip, avocado mixture, sour cream mixture, onions, tomatoes, olives and cheese.
Eat with tortilla chips.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix first three ingredients and spread on a dish.
top with remaining ingredients.
Serve with Fritos Scoops.

title: apple chips
directions: In a large skillet, combine apple juice and cinnamon stick. Bring to a boil.
Slice 1/2-inch from tops and bottoms of the apples and discard. Stand the apples on either cut and saw gently crosswise into very thin rings, rotating the apple
as necessary to get even. Drop apples slices into the boiling juice. Cook 4 to 5 minutes or until slices are translucent and lightly golden.

title: easy filled date cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla and milk.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased pan.
Place 1/2 teaspoon filling on dough.
Place another teaspoon dough on top of filling.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Combine all ingredients. Serve at once. Be sure you use firm tomatoes.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown hamburg and onion.
Pour off fat, blend in pizza sauce and garlic powder.
Put mixture in 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, oil, salt and flour.
Pour over meat mixture and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. (Mushrooms, bell pepper strips, Italian sausage or Canadian bacon can be added.) Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: carrot salad
directions: Put carrots, onion and green pepper in bowl.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Store in refrigerator in tightly covered container.
Makes about 1 3/4 cups dressing. Enjoy over your favorite salad.

title: dump cake
directions: Melt butter in Pyrex dish.
Combine ingredients and pour into dish.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes, until done.

title: salmon rolls
directions: Mix biscuits according to directions on package.
Roll into oblong shape.
Brush with melted butter or margarine.
Sprinkle with dehydrated onions, lemon juice, lemon pepper, paprika and parsley or cilantro.
Add cleaned, flaked salmon.
Roll in jelly roll fashion and slice about 1-inch thick.
Place on baking sheet and brush with melted butter or margarine.
Bake according to package directions for biscuits.
Serve with Cheese Sauce for Salmon Rolls.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Have cookie sheets ready.
With wooden spoon, stir peanut butter, sugar and eggs until blended (dough will be slightly sticky).
With floured hands, roll level tablespoonfuls into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Place 1 1/2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes until cookies look dry and tops are cracked.
Remove from oven and immediately press chocolate kiss in center of each.
Cool on cookie sheet for 1 to 2 minutes, then remove to wire racks.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: sausage balls
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mary's squash pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Pour into 9-inch pastry lined pie pan.
Bake at 425° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all except sunflower seeds and raisins.
Put those in just before serving.
Serves 6 or 8.

title: cereal crunch
directions: Mix the cereal and peanuts in large bowl.
Melt almond bark and peanut butter.
Pour over cereal and peanuts.
Mix until all cereal is coated.
Drop bite-sized pieces on wax paper with spoon or press into pan and cut into squares.

title: lemon nut sandwich spread
directions: Combine lemon juice and rind, sugar, egg yolks and butter. Cook in double boiler, stirring until thick.
Cool; stir in nuts.

title: never-fail pie crust
directions: Blend dry ingredients with shortening.
Add egg and liquids. Form into a roll.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Store in refrigerator. Take out as much as needed.
Warm in room temperature.
Roll out on floured board.
Makes enough for at least 3 pies.

title: easy coconut custard pie
directions: Put all ingredients, except coconut, in blender.
Blend on low for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 10-inch pie pan.
Let set for 5 minutes, then sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pineapple fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple (save juice).
Mix flour and sugar.
Add juice and egg.
Cook until it coats the spoon.
Cool, then pour over fruit.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Clean and cut broccoli into bite size pieces.
In a large bowl, combine broccoli, onion, raisins and bacon bits.
In smaller bowl, mix mayo, sugar and vinegar.
Pour liquid over broccoli and toss to coat.
Serves 4 to 6 as side dish.

title: special potato soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter in Dutch oven until tender. Add next 7 ingredients.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until tender.
Remove from heat and mash with potato masher.
Add milk and cheese.
Cook, stirring constantly, until cheese melts.
Yields 5 cups.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Be sure hash browns are thoroughly thawed.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch glass casserole at 350° for 1 hour until bubbly and brown.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken curry(makes 4 servings)
directions: In small saucepan, over low heat, cook onion, apple and curry powder in margarine until tender.
Stir in soup, half and half and steak sauce; set aside.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Best to serve cold.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: In 1-quart heatproof casserole, combine refried beans, chilies, onion, olives and chili powder.
Top with an avocado that has been mashed with the lemon juice, crushed garlic clove and hot sauce. Over that, spread the sour cream and sprinkle with the Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, until hot and bubbly.
Serve with chips.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage until done.
Drain well.
Add all other ingredients except stuffing and stir well.
Cover with stuffing. Bake 350° for 1 hr. or until "set".

title: tuna pate
directions: Blend softened cream cheese, chili sauce, parsley, onion and hot pepper sauce; gradually stir in drained tuna.
Beat until mixture is thoroughly blended.
Pack in a 4-cup greased mold or small bowl.
Chill thoroughly, at least 3 hours or overnight.
At serving time unmold on serving plate.
If desired, garnish with sliced green olives and/or greens.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients. Roll into balls. Place on 9 x 13 pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: four egg dish
directions: Butter one side of each piece of bread.
Place 8 slices of bread with butter side up at the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Place ham and cheese on top of bread slices.
Place last 8 slices of bread with buttered side down on top of ham and cheese.
Beat eggs, add milk and pour over bread, ham and cheese.
Cover pan and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in the morning at 300° for 1 hour.

title: dump cake
directions: Melt butter in bottom of the baking pan.
Dump cherry pie filling in pineapple.
Place together in 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Spread dry cake mix over filling and cut into the filling mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
This is so easy to make to be so good.

title: thelma and juanita's made up cake
directions: Mix together all but apple butter or preserves.
Then pour apple butter or whatever you use in on top of the cake mix you pour in pan.
Just use half.
Do the other half the same way. Bake until golden brown at 200°.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; don't overcook.
Drain and rinse.
Add enough salad dressing to moisten well.
Add Supreme seasoning until spaghetti is brightly colored.
The amount of vegetables to add is your preference.
Chill before serving.

title: divinity
directions: Cook first three ingredients in large pan.
Cook until hard ball stage (255°).
Beat egg whites until stiff, then add cooked ingredients to your egg whites.
Beat until candy loses gloss color, then drop by spoons onto wax paper.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger; season with salt and pepper.
Combine all ingredients.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: party potato casserole
directions: Two hours before serving, cook potatoes in water until fork-tender.
Cool slightly; peel.
Mix at low speed, potatoes, sour cream, milk, 2 tablespoons butter, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper until smooth and fluffy.
Set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, mix well squash with 1 tablespoon butter and 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Set aside.
In another small bowl, beat egg slightly.
Add spinach, onion, 1 tablespoon butter and 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Mix well; set aside.
In 2-quart deep dish, evenly layer mashed potato mixture with squash and spinach mixtures.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until heated through.
Remove from heat and sprinkle with cheese; let stand until cheese melts.
Yields 10 servings.

title: teriyaki chicken and rice(all day cooking)
directions: In crock-pot place chicken, teriyaki sauce and water.
Cook on low during the day.
Make sure you put enough water to last for several hours. Spoon out serving of cooked rice.
Top with pieces of seasoned chicken and juice from pot.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons butter; add flour and blend.
Add chicken broth, poultry seasoning, salt and pepper to taste.
Blend and cook to a thin, smooth sauce.
Cook spaghetti.
Saute mushrooms in the 1/4 cup butter.
Add spaghetti, well drained, and sauteed mushrooms to the sauce.
Mix in chicken and cheese and bake in a buttered casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.
(If you wish, reserve half the cheese for last minute browning on top of the casserole.)

title: cheese bubble loaf
directions: Cover dough and let rise in warm place until doubled.
Divide in 32 equal pieces.
Shape each into a ball around a cube of cheese.
Pinch to seal.
Dip balls in melted margarine.
Layer, seam side down, in greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pan or round pan (whatever).
Cover and let rise until doubled.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes, until top is firm and golden brown.
Remove from pan and serve warm.

title: cheesie cheese crackers
directions: You will need a pan
that will hold 40 Zesta crackers.
Spray pan with Pam.
Place crackers in pan with sides touching.
Grate the extra sharp Cheddar (pregrated doesn't work).
Sprinkle lightly with red pepper.
Using lowest oven rack, broil until cheese stops bubbling
(15 to 18 minutes).
Remove from oven. Turn it off.
Wait 10 minutes and put pan back in oven for 5 hours or overnight on warm.

title: marinated carrots(copper pennies)
directions: Bring to a boil and cool.
Pour over carrots, onion and peppers.
Let stand 24 hours.
(Garbanzo beans can be substituted for carrots.)

title: pineapple-berry bowl
directions: In glass bowl, arrange strawberries, then pineapple chunks. Top with raspberries. Pour chilled pineapple syrup over. Serve with cream. Serves 6.

title: pepsi beef
directions: Trim excess fat from beef.
Prick beef on all sides with a fork.
Rub in garlic powder and onion soup mix.
Pour Pepsi over and under meat; cover with foil.
Bake for 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 hours at 325°.
Cool and refrigerate overnight in the original pan.
Next day, skim off solidified fat that has formed on liquid.
Slice meat and reheat in juices.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Line 9-inch pie plate with pie crust.
Arrange slices of cheese and bacon in overlapping layers in pie crust.
Beat eggs with flour, generous grating of nutmeg and cayenne to taste.
Add cream and melted butter.
Pour this mixture over bacon and cheese and bake in 350° oven until custard is set and lightly browned, about 40 minutes.

title: heavenly chicken casserole
directions: Toss.
Put in a large, shallow dish.
Top with 2 cups of corn flakes, tossed in 1/3 cup melted butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: make ahead potato casserole
directions: Whip potatoes and butter.
Add remaining ingredients and whip until mixture is light and fluffy.
Place in buttered casserole and sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Dot with small pieces of butter.
At this point, you can refrigerate (can be prepared 1 to 2 days ahead).
Bring to room temperature before baking at 325°, uncovered, for about 25 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Steam the squash and onion in a small amount of water until tender. Drain well and mash. Add other ingredients except cracker crumbs and butter.
Mix well. Pour into oiled dish. Can be frozen. When ready to bake, top with cracker crumbs and a small amount of melted butter.

title: grandma's sugar 'n' spice cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar, egg and molasses. Sift together the dry ingredients and add to first mixture. Mix well. Form into balls the size of walnuts. Place about 2-inches apart on baking pan. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350° (do not overbake). Roll in confectioners sugar while warm.

title: fruit salad
directions: In mixing bowl, toss together the oranges and apples.
Cover and chill. Combine the shredded lettuce and celery in serving bowl.
Cover and chill.
At serving time, toss fruit mixture with sliced bananas.
Transfer mixture with a spoon.
Sprinkle pecans atop.
Arrange tomatoes on top of salad.
Garnish with celery leaves.

title: margarita mix slush
directions: Mix together in large container.
Freeze.
When blending, add a scoop of two in a blender and add a little 7-Up for your taste.

title: creamy sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: "potato" cookies
directions: Mix butter, milk, cocoa and syrup together by hand.
Save 2 tablespoons for decorating.
Add graham cracker crumbs; mix well. Shape into 10 pieces to look like small potatoes.
Put onto plate. Let stay in refrigerator for 30 minutes, then sprinkle with cocoa.
Make indentations in cookies; use reserved cream mixture to make like sprouts.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine 2 cups flour and 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Cut butter into flour mixture with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Spoon flour mixture into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Press firmly and evenly into pan using fingertips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until crust is lightly browned. Combine remaining 1/2 cup flour and baking powder.
Set aside. Combine eggs, 2 cups sugar, lemon rind (if desired) and lemon juice.
Stir well.
Stir dry ingredients into egg mixture and pour over baked crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned and set.
Cool on a wire rack.
Dust lightly with powdered sugar and cut into bars.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Dice meats (any two meats can be used).
Dice tomato and cheese.
Mix diced ingredients with spaghetti.
Sprinkle dry mix over diced ingredients and spaghetti.
Toss with bottle dressing and chill.

title: chocolate macaroon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar, cocoa and margarine.
Press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: honey pecan chicken
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Add pecans.
Simmer over medium heat for 35 to 45 minutes until sauce is thickened, like a caramel sauce.
Charboil boneless skinless chicken breasts. Pour enough sauce over the chicken to cover.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Rinse well and drain again.
Add green pepper and sliced onion to the beans.
Mix other ingredients and add to the bean mixture.
Mix well and store in the refrigerator overnight.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding with 1 cup pineapple juice and 1 cup peach juice. Stir until it thickens.
Add all fruits and nuts.
Chill.
When ready to serve, fold in Cool Whip.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mash avocado and spread on the bottom of an 8 x 8-inch serving dish with sides.
Spread sour cream carefully on top of avocado layer.
Drizzle taco sauce on sour cream.
Sprinkle onion over all, then cover with cheese.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Can be made one day ahead.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Stick 3 or 4 chips into dip.

title: peanut butter and jelly cake
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter.
Gradually add eggs, one at a time.
Beat at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in vanilla. Pour into two greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool completely.
Spread jelly between layers.
Frost sides and top with Peanut Butter Frosting.

title: avocado egg salad
directions: Combine eggs, bacon and onion.
Cut and scoop avocado pulp and mash with a fork or large plate.
Stir in mayonnaise, lemon juice, prepared mustard and salt.
Add egg mixture; spoon into pretty glass cups.
Garnish with leaf of lettuce.

title: traditional russian easter bread
directions: Put yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water and 1/2 teaspoon sugar. Set aside in warm place until a little bubbly.
Heat milk and water to lukewarm; add yeast mixture and mix well.
Measure 4 cups of flour into bowl; add liquid and mix well, using mixer.
Set aside, covered, in a warm place for 1 hour, then melt margarine and beat eggs.
Add sugar, salt, margarine and eggs to raised dough.
Then add remaining flour, a little at a time, kneading until hands are clean.
Put in warm place, covered, and let rise again until double in bulk.
Grease seven 2-pound coffee cans well.
Fill half full. Again, put in warm place to rise to top of cans.
Beat whole egg with very small amount of water and brush over tops of breads and bake in 325° to 350° oven for 45 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: karen's chili
directions: Brown hamburger and drain well. Add all other ingredients and simmer an hour or longer.

title: chocolate chip date cakes
directions: Can substitute margarine for butter or use equal amounts.

title: company chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: amaretto slush
directions: Combine sugar and water in a saucepan, stirring well.
Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Combine sugar mixture, lemonade and Amaretto; stir well and freeze
mixture overnight.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, mix the first 4 ingredients. Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly, (I use a wooden spoon) on high heat. Set heat on medium (enough to keep boiling, but not scorch) for 6 minutes, without stirring.
Test for soft ball in cool water. Remove from heat and let cool for 10 minutes. Add margarine, salt and vanilla. Beat (approximately 8 to 10 minutes) until mixture begins to thicken.
Add walnuts, if desired, while beating. Quickly pour onto a platter (prepared with a paper towel under plastic wrap; the towel keeps the wrap from sticking to the platter).
Let cool thoroughly.
Cut into pieces with a pizza cutter.

title: cream of onion soup
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in onions and garlic.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes or until onions are soft and lightly browned, stirring frequently.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Stir in milk and broth.
Cook, uncovered, 8 to 12 minutes or until thickened and thoroughly heated, stirring frequently.
Do not boil.
Garnish with parsley.

title: corn pudding
directions: Stir into corn the flour, sugar, salt and butter.
Beat eggs well, add to milk.
Combine mixtures.
Pour into 2-quart casserole. Stir from bottom several times during cooking.
Bake at 350° until set in center.

title: chewy oatmeal cookie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheet with butter flavor Crisco.
Combine butter flavor Crisco, light brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Combine oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix into creamed mixture at low speed just until blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 2-inches apart onto baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet.
Remove to kitchen counter.

title: salmon chowder
directions: Cook potatoes, carrots, onion, celery, salt, water and butter. Add corn, salmon, milk, Worcestershire sauce and flour with milk. Bring to boil and serve.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Blend cream cheese, mayo and sugar.
Add pecans and cranberries.
Blend well.
Fold in whipped topping.
Put in 9 x 9-inch dish and freeze.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, beat well.
Sift together flour, salt, soda, baking powder and spices; add to creamed mixture, alternating with the applesauce. Beat well after each addition.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Spread batter into a greased 13 x 9 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion together.
Add the taco sauce to the browned beef and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Mix salad ingredients.
When ready to serve, place the crushed tortillas/Doritos chips on salad and pour hot meat sauce over.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into an ungreased 9 x 9 pan. Make three holes in the dry mixture. In the first hole, pour the vanilla. In the second hole, pour the vinegar. In the third hole, pour the melted butter. Pour the water over the whole thing and mix thoroughly.

title: corn pie
directions: Blend 1 cup cracker crumbs and 1/2 cup melted butter and press evenly on bottom and sides of baking dish.
Cook pepper and onion in 2 T butter until onion is transparent.
Blend in the flour and cook until bubbly.
Add the milk and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add the corn, salt, sugar and eggs. Mix well and pour into the crust.
Top with remaining crumbs. Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes or until firm.

title: momo's seasoned potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch slices.
Boil until tender (do not add any salt).
Pour off water, leaving about 2 inches in bottom of pan.
Melt butter.
Add to butter the seasoned salt and flour, stirring constantly.
Add evaporated milk; stir until boils.
Pour over cooked potatoes (and left over water) and let simmer for couple of minutes.

title: squirrel jambalaya
directions: Brown squirrels in iron pot.
When brown, pour off grease and add chopped onion, celery and bell peppers; then saute.
Cover with water and cook until tender.
Then add rice to squirrel and gravy. Gravy should be 2 to 2 1/2 cups liquid.
Cover and cook on low heat about 1/2 hour until rice is done.
Stir once or twice.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets, reserving liquid.
In liquid, mix remaining ingredients.
Cook on stove until mixture thickens.
Pour over beets.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice with water until fluffy.
In a separate frying pan; fry eggs flat, then cut them into tiny strips.
Remove from pan. Add remaining ingredients to pan and saute a few minutes.
Then add rice and eggs into mixture and season with salt, pepper and soy sauce.
Mix thoroughly.

title: liver and onion supreme
directions: Slice liver into thin strips, removing veins and membranes. Combine flour, paprika, thyme, salt and pepper in a paper bag. Coat liver with seasoned flour.
Fry quickly in a little oil over medium heat, turning to prevent overcooking.
Do not overcook as it will be dry and tough.
Serve with fried onions.

title: overnight cinnamon sticky buns
directions: Sprinkle nuts and raisins in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Arrange frozen rolls over nuts and raisins.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
In small bowl, combine pudding mix, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Sprinkle over rolls.
Top with butter pieces.

title: pickled green beans
directions: To each gallon of fresh green beans add vinegar and sugar. Cover with water and cook for 30 to 40 minutes.
Pack in quart jars with 1 tablespoon salt per jar.
Seal.
Rinse beans thoroughly before cooking.

title: lasagna
directions: Sauce:
Brown lightly in a large heavy pan with olive oil the beef and sausage, breaking meat apart while browning.
After meat is done add onion and garlic, cook together and then add tomatoes, tomato sauce, fresh parsley, basil and wine.
Rinse cans out with little water, add to sauce.
Add salt and pepper.
Simmer for a few hours, the longer the thicker and better, stirring occasionally.

title: caldillo(mexican stew)
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Transfer to a soup kettle and add remaining ingredients and cook until potatoes are soft.
For hotter stew, add more picante sauce.
Great meal on a cold day served with flour tortillas.

title: artichoke dip
directions: In food processor, combine cream cheese, milk, Parmesan, scallions, garlic, eggs and lemon juice.
Pulse until smooth.
Add the artichokes, salt, pepper and cayenne and pulse just until mixed but still chunky.
Transfer the mixture to a buttered deep 4 cup casserole dish and blake until lightly browned and set, about 1 hour.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: potato casserole
directions: Put washed, unpeeled potatoes in boiling water with bay leaf and boil until tender.
Let cool.
Preheat oven to 325 F.
Peel potatoes and coarsely grate, add melted butter, sour cream and soup.
Stir until smooth.
Add green onions and half of cheese. Cover and bake for 45 minutes.
Remove cover and add remaining cheese, then bake at 350 F for 15 minutes or until top is browned.

title: alston's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add salt.
Gradually add sugar.
Fold in butter and syrup and
fold
in
vanilla. Heat oven to 450°.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add
pecans.
Change oven to 275°. Bake for 40 minutes or until pie
is
brown
and done in middle.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown the meat and drain.
Add onion, taco seasoning, olives and enchilada sauce to meat.
Cook for a few minutes in skillet. Use a 2-quart baking dish; put in one layer of tortillas.
Spoon some meat mixture over tortillas and sprinkle with cheese.
Repeat to make 3 to 4 layers.
Add 1/2 cup water and cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian baked pork
directions: Place pineapple with juice in a large greased baking dish. Place sliced potatoes over pineapple.
Sprinkle with brown sugar. Place pork chops on top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.
Uncover.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: crust for cobbler
directions: Combine all ingredients but fruit; pour batter in baking dish; add fruit.

title: molasses nog
directions: Combine milk, water, salt and molasses; stir well.
Pour into glasses and sprinkle a dash of preferred spice.
Stir.
Serves 5.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: date nut bread
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and set aside.
In a large bowl, sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in the brown sugar.
Place the egg in a mixing bowl and beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in the milk, vanilla and melted margarine, mixing until blended.
Stir this mixture into the sifted dry ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Fold in the chopped dates and nuts.
Spoon the batter into the prepared pan and bake about 40 minutes or until the bread begins to pull away from the sides of the pan and the center is done when tested.
Let cool in the pan.
To serve, slice the bread and cut each slice lengthwise into halves.
Place the whipped cream cheese on top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix broth with can of soup.
Place chicken in casserole dish. Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle with Italian bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until bubbly hot.

title: bernie's chinese wings
directions: On small salad plates, one plate for one serving, arrange a large leaf of lettuce, which covers most of the plate.
Slice and arrange three thin slices of ripe tomato and three thin slices of fresh "Mozzarella di buffala" cheese on the center of the plate. Add olive oil, salt and pepper.
On the sides of the plate, add a few sun-dried tomatoes, various kinds of olives, and a small portion of Prosciutto ham.
Simple and easy, this is an attractive and delicious appetizer for pasta dishes or chicken dishes.
Buon appetito!!!

title: pineapple angel cake
directions: Combine cake mix and pineapple. Mix according to package directions. Pour into 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until dark golden brown. Frost with Cool Whip when cool.

title: apple custard pie
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add beaten eggs, applesauce and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked crust and bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until done.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Prepare 9-inch baked pie shell.
Whip Dream Whip according to directions.
Prepare vanilla pudding using 1 1/2 cups milk.
Add Dream Whip, peanut butter and vanilla to prepared pudding.
Pour into pie shell and cool.
Sprinkle with crushed peanuts.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sugar and relish in small bowl; mix well. Let set while shredding and grating. Combine all and mix well. Refrigerate. Stir before serving.

title: shoe peg corn
directions: Mix vegetables, soup, sour cream, onion, cheese and pepper together.
Top with margarine, almonds and Ritz.
Bake 325°
for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 qts.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, apples, oil and salt.
Allow to stand 20 minutes.
Mix other ingredients together.
Combine with apple mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to directions on package.
Drain and put into greased casserole.
Next, mix onion, celery, cheese and mayonnaise.
Spread over vegetables.
Next, melt butter and mix with crackers.
Spread on top of casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Prepare crackers.
Scald milk and butter.
Add salt and pepper.
Gradually pour over beaten eggs, stirring constantly. Add corn and mix well.
Add crackers and mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot rice
directions: Mix rice, butter and sour cream together.
In a greased casserole dish, place a layer of rice, then a layer of peppers and a layer of cheese.
Repeat, following steps.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Put butter in a cold skillet.
Add garlic and mash with sugar, salt and pepper.
Cook until butter is melted.
Add meat and brown.
Add tomato sauce and simmer, uncovered, for about 20 minutes.
Cook spaghetti.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream and green onions.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: dirt cake
directions: Put cookies through food processor.
Make pudding and let sit for 5 minutes.
Stir in Cool Whip and 1/2 of cookies.
Layer cookies and pudding, ending with cookies on top.

title: ranch biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Cool and add to the following mixture:
oil, sugar, salt, buttermilk and flour.
Stir and let set overnight, tightly covered in refrigerator.
Pinch off needed amount of dough and knead on floured surface.
Roll out and make into biscuits or pinch off and shape by hand into roll.
Let rise about 1/2 hour.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Dough will keep in refrigerator one week, tightly sealed.

title: squash appetizer
directions: Beat eggs.
Cut squash and grate onion.
Put everything together in bowl and mix.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put squash mixture in pan and bake in oven at 350° for about 3/4 hour.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Spray wok or heavy skillet with Pam.
Heat until hot.
Add chicken and stir-fry just until chicken turns white.
Remove and save.
Add celery, mushrooms, onion, water chestnuts, bamboo shoots, ginger and oyster sauce to skillet.
Cook over high heat for 3 minutes.
Drain pineapple.
Add juice, 3/4 cup of the chicken broth and the chicken to wok; cover and simmer 2 minutes. Combine remaining 1/4 cup chicken broth and the cornstarch; blend until smooth.
Stir into wok.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Add pineapple tidbits; heat just until piping hot.

title: basic beer batter
directions: Combine egg yolks and beer, blending well.
Beat in flour, cornstarch and salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Beat egg whites until almost firm and whisk into batter.
Dip fillets of the food (fish, veal, etc.) into batter and follow cooking procedure for the particular dish you are preparing.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in churn and fill rest with 2% or whole milk.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Peel and quarter tomatoes.

Add onion, celery and green pepper. Cook until juicy and tender. Add sugar, butter and croutons. Pour into greased 1-quart baking dish. Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes. Top with grated Cheddar cheese and return to oven to melt.

title: garlic pepper cheese ball
directions: Mix above together.
Form 2 balls.
Cover balls with garlic pepper and Lawry's seasoned pepper.
(Lots of pepper is necessary!)

title: lucky seven rolls
directions: Pour milk over sugar, shortening and salt in a mixing bowl. Cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in lukewarm water; add egg and mix well.
Add to milk mixture.
Add about half the flour to yeast mixture and beat thoroughly.
Add remaining flour; mix well. Knead on a lightly floured board until smooth and elastic (about 5 minutes).
Place dough in a greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until double about 1 hour.
Shape as desired.
Let rise again.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate crackles(microwave)
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine butter and chocolate.
Microwave at 50% (Medium) for 1 to 4 minutes, or until melted; blend well. Beat in granulated sugar, eggs, baking powder, vanilla and salt. Stir in flour and nuts.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 8 hours.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Roll crackers.
Use half to cover bottom of well-greased casserole.
Slice eggs over crumbs.
Arrange asparagus in next layer.
Add dried beef, cut into small pieces.
Add liquid from asparagus to mushroom soup.
Scald milk, stir into mixture and pour over layers.
Grate cheese coarsely over top.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Brown top under broiler, if necessary.
May substitute 1 cup cooked chicken, if desired.

title: medium white sauce
directions: Melt margarine in skillet; blend in flour until smooth, stirring.
Add milk gradually; cook until thick and smooth, stirring.

title: self-rising cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Add shortening and a little over half of the milk to which the flavoring has been added.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Add rest of milk and 2 eggs; beat for 2 minutes. Put into greased pans; cook at 375° for 30 minutes, or until done.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Put cleaned strawberries in baked pie shell.
Add first 6 ingredients together in a saucepan.
Cook over medium-high heat until thick; set aside to cool.
Add the rest of the ingredients and pour over strawberries.
Let set about 1 hour in refrigerator before serving.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Place potatoes in bottom of 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Layer butter, onion, beans, rice, green pepper, tomatoes and ground beef (pre-cook enough to drain fat) over potatoes; season with salt and pepper as desired.
Cover evenly with soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cover the last 30 minutes.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.

title: chocolate supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients together and press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes;	let cool.

title: cream of asparagus soup
directions: *Make thin white sauce using 3/4 ounce butter, 3/4 ounce flour and a little cream.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt and baking soda. In separate bowl, mix oil, eggs and carrots.
Combine both mixtures.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Whip cream cheese with milk.
Set aside.
Add water to pineapple juice to make 2 cups.
Heat and then dissolve jello in it.
Cool.
When beginning to set, mix with cream cheese mixture. Garnish with nuts.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and cube.
Add all other ingredients and pour in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
For added flavor, refrigerate several hours before baking.
I've prepared this the day before and refrigerated overnight, then baked and served.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Cream the cream cheese with mixer; add cherries and juice. Remove mixer and add fruit cocktail and pineapple; mix well.
Fold in cool Whip and marshmallows.
May add 1/2 cup pecans (optional).

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and shortening. Add sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add vanilla. Sift all dry ingredients together. Add dry ingredients and milk alternately to creamed mixture.
Bake in 10-inch tube pan (greased and floured) for 80 minutes at 325°.

title: snow peas
directions: Tip and string the fresh peas if necessary. Defrost peas if frozen. Heat the butter or oil in a pan and add the peas and ginger. Saute until done. Won't take but a few minutes. Season with salt and pepper. Serves 4 to 6.

title: summertime zucchini saute
directions: In 10-inch skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Stir in onion, salt, basil leaves and garlic powder.
Cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally until onion is crisply-tender (4 to 5 minutes).
Stir in zucchini.
Continue cooking, stirring constantly, until heated through (2 to 3 minutes).
Sprinkle tomatoes, olives and cheese over zucchini.
Cover.
Cook 2 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 5 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: shrimp chowder
directions: Combine and blend all ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 15 minutes.
Can also use tuna, clams or crab meat.

title: carrot cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix the flour, sugar, oil, baking soda, cinnamon, eggs, grated carrots and vanilla together. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: sandwich cookies
directions: In a medium bowl, combine 1/2 cup of the powdered sugar and marshmallow cream; mix well. On powdered sugar surface, knead in remaining powdered sugar. Shape mixture into two 8-inch ropes. Cut off small pieces and place one at a time between 2 cookies.

title: barbecued sausage
directions: Cut a Hillshire Farm smoked sausage link into 2-inch serving pieces.
Cover in saucepan with water and boil 10 to 15 minutes. Drain and cover with your favorite barbecue sauce.
Simmer until sauce thickens.

title: pull-apart bacon cheese wreath
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut a 12-inch square of aluminum foil and press on bottom and sides of 9-inch round cake pan.
Place inverted 3 1/2-inch custard cup in center of pan.
Lightly grease foil and sides of custard cup; set aside.
Melt butter or oleo and cheese spread in small saucepan on low heat (mixture may appear curdled).
Remove from heat and stir vigorously until smooth and creamy.
Spread to cover bottom of pan around custard cup.
Cut each biscuit into quarters and fit pieces into pan around custard cup to form "wreath."
Bake at 450° for 14 minutes (top will be brown).
Turn over onto serving platter.
Remove foil and custard cup.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon and parsley.
Serve warm.
Makes about 40 appetizers.

title: italian roast
directions: In foil-lined pan, place roast in foil. Pour bottle of Italian dressing over roast. Cover and place in oven at 300° for 2 to 3 hours.

title: chicken apricot
directions: Mix and spread over skinned chicken breast.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar, cheese and flour together.
Put in buttered dish.
Cover with crumbs. Drizzle butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: orange cottage cheese fluff
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add and fold in Cool Whip.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: super spud casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Put grated cheese on top. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes large casserole.

title: pasta con broccoli
directions: Cook noodles and put aside.
Brown chicken, onion, bacon and butter.
Add half and half, Lawry's seasoning, garlic and pepper. Bring to a boil.
Add broccoli and noodles; bring to a boil.
Add Parmesan cheese.

title: country steak
directions: Flour, salt and pepper steak.
Fry until brown.
Place steak, onions, mushroom soup and water in a slow cooker.
Cook on medium for 4 hours.

title: successful meringue
directions: Moisten cornstarch in small amount of water.
Stir in boiling water.
Cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add salt, then add sugar gradually.
Beat in the cooked and cooled cornstarch until firm peaks form.
Brown 10 minutes at 425°.
Makes enough meringue for 2 pies.
This holds up with no weeping.

title: casserole of pork chops or chicken on rice
directions: Grease skillet.
Brown meat on both sides.
Season with salt and pepper.
Combine rice, onion, celery, soup and milk.
Put rice in greased casserole dish; lay meat on top.
Drizzle a little meat juice that cooked out on top.
Cover.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes or longer.
Serves 4.

title: squash souffle
directions: Drain squash except for 1/2 cup liquid.
Add carrots, pimientos, onion, sour cream, cream of chicken soup and 1 cup Cheddar cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Mix 3/4 stuffing with melted butter.
Line casserole, pouring squash and sprinkle with remaining 1/4 stuffing and 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: swiss 'n' chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except walnuts.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake 40 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter haystacks(microwave)
directions: Place chips and peanut butter in 2-quart casserole or bowl. Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave at 50% power (Medium) for 3 to 5 minutes, until most of chips are shiny or soft.
Blend well. Stir in peanuts and chow mein noodles with rubber spatula.
Drop by forkfuls onto wax paper.
Cool until set.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix hot water and margarine in bowl. Stir in stuffing mix, pepper and half of pipneapple.
Spoon stuffing evenly on chicken and roll tightly.
Secure with toothpicks. Place in 9-inch square pan with remaining stuffing in center.
Mix remaining pineapple with sugar, vinegar and ginger.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake 35 minutes or until chicken is thoroughly cooked.

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in skin, cool, peel and coarsely shred on grater.
In saucepan, over low heat, combine cheese and butter, stirring constantly, until almost melted.
Remove from heat. Blend in sour cream, onions, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes; stir lightly.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mash avocados with lemon juice. Add other ingredients. Seal tightly and refrigerate until serving. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Cream together in large bowl the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Beat until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add almond extract.
Add flour and baking powder.
Beat well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon onto top of batter 16 spoons of pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown and cake is done.

title: rice and vegetable casserole
directions: Boil rice until soft and drain. Put a half stick of butter in rice for seasoning and to keep moist. Chop up vegetables and saut them in pan with butter When vegetables are almost soft, add your rice. Mix together. In a casserole pan, add a layer of rice and vegetables and sprinkle over with shredded cheese. Keep doing this until you don't have any more rice and vegetables left. Then put the last layer with cheese.

title: veal scallopini
directions: Wipe meat with cloth. Rub with seasoned flour.
Heat oil in heavy skillet. Add veal and garlic.
Cook until meat is browned. Remove garlic.
Add wine and remaining ingredients and simmer for 45 to 55 minutes or until tender.
Serve meat with sauce left in the pan, adding a little water, if desired, to increase amount of sauce.
Serves 6.

title: hot ham and cheese sandwich
directions: Combine all ingredients with mixed mayonnaise and chilli sauce.
Mix well; spread in split rolls.
Wrap each bun in aluminum foil.
Twist ends and heat at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: biscuits and salsa
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters.
Layer biscuits in 8 or 9-inch round pan.
Spoon salsa over biscuits.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Continue layering biscuits and salsa.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 400° until browned.

title: borscht
directions: American way Russian soup.
Quantity of beets to same quantity of water.
Blend beets, sliced medium size, water and lemon juice in blender.
Add remaining ingredients and chill.
Serve chilled.

title: pasta with peas and ham
directions: Cook and drain pasta. Add milk and most of the cheese.
Salt and pepper.
Toss until the cheese melts. Sprinkle individual servings with remaining cheese.

title: pumpkin ring cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour Bundt pan. Beat all ingredients on medium speed. Bake 50 minutes.

title: hot ham sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Butter buns and spread mixture on them.
Wrap in foil.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: ham and cheese souffle
directions: Layer half the bread cubes, ham, cheeses and remaining bread cubes in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Beat eggs, milk and seasonings in bowl.
Pour over layers.
Chill overnight.
Combine cornflakes and butter in bowl.
Sprinkle over layers.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Wash mushrooms.
Slice and simmer 5 minutes (in large skillet) with 1 tablespoon butter along with the onion and celery.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour, sugar and salt.
Combine egg, water and vinegar.
Pour liquid into flour mixture all at once.
Blend with a spoon just until flour is moistened.
This is an easy crust to handle and can be re-rolled without toughening.
Keeps in refrigerator up to 2 weeks.
Makes 2 crusts or 1 top and 1 bottom.

title: pronto pups
directions: Mix all
dry
ingredients
together.
Add egg and milk; beat until smooth.
Dip	franks	in batter and fry in hot deep oil until brown.
Serve hot with mustard.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and drain.
Mix in large bowl all ingredients. Mix well.
Put in long baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: parmesan bread deluxe
directions: In a small bowl, combine cheese, salad dressing and onion. Spread a generous teaspoon of the dressing mixture onto one side of each of the bread slices.
Arrange bread, dressing side up, on cookie sheets. Broil 4-inches from heat for 2 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 24 slices.
Reheat leftover bread on the grill or in a microwave oven.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place the cooked and drained broccoli in an 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Slice Velveeta; put all over top of broccoli. Dot with butter.
Crush the crackers.
Melt the oleo; mix with crackers and sprinkle on top of cheese.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and milk.
Add dry pudding then cool whip. Pour into pie crust.
Chill and serve.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Lightly pack into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Cream lard and sugar, blend in molasses, sour cream and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Roll out on generously floured surface.
Cut.
Bake in 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar and egg.
Stir in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Chill dough.
Roll in balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: red onion marmalade
directions: Add all ingredients in a non-corrosive saucepan.
Cook at low heat until liquid is completely reduced.
Stir in cracked black pepper to taste.
Chill.
Use as an accompaniment to grilled chicken or hamburgers.

title: coconut-pineapple pie
directions: Melt butter, then add other ingredients.
Mix well and pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° until firm about 45 minutes.

title: crunchy beef bake
directions: Cook macaroni.
Brown ground beef.
Combine all ingredients, but onions.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or longer.
Uncover.
Top with onion rings and bake 5 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: jogging in a glass
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drink 6 ounces a day.
Good for high blood pressure, high cholesterol and arthritis.
(It works, I drink it everyday.)

title: beefy skillet dinner
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef and onion without added fat until beef is crumbly.
Drain excess fat.
Add tomatoes and grits. Stir to blend well.
Bring to a boil, lower heat and simmer, stirring occasionally for 5 minutes.
Stir in green beans.
Add salt and pepper.
Reheat until bubbly.

title: microwave creamy scrambled eggs
directions: Combine all ingredients except cream cheese in casserole. Beat until well mixed.
Stir in cream cheese.
Mix well.
Cover. Microwave on High 6 to 8 minutes.
Stir every 2 minutes.
After cooking, let stand 2 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Microwave for 3 minutes on High.
Remove and stir constantly. Microwave 2 more minutes; remove and stir.
Microwave 2 more minutes; stir.
Add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Mix well.
Pour into pan to cool.

title: broiled chicken
directions: Remove all skin from chicken.
Whisk egg, milk and salt.
Roll chicken in egg mix, then bread crumbs.
Place on broiling pan in bottom half of oven.
Watch closely and turn often to prevent burning.
Chicken is done when clear fluid runs as it is pierced with a knife.

title: sweet and sour wieners
directions: Combine sugar, flour, mustard, vinegar, soy sauce and juice in a small saucepan and heat to boiling, stirring until all ingredients are thoroughly blended.
Add wieners and serve.

title: crock-pot steak and gravy
directions: Cut steak into single serving pieces. Sprinkle with garlic powder and pepper. In crock-pot, layer half the steak, onion, 1 can of soup and 1 package of soup mix. Repeat with remaining ingredients. Add water. Cook on low heat 6 to 8 hours.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: Combine margarine and cocoa in a saucepan.
Add 1 cup water; bring to a boil, stirring constantly over medium heat.
Remove from stove.
Combine flour, sugar, soda and salt in bowl.
Stir in eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add to cocoa mixture.
Mix until blended.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes in 15 x 13-inch pan or 25 minutes in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Frost with a peanut butter or chocolate frosting.

title: chicken gumbo with rice
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Wash good in cold water.
Pat dry.
Heat 2 tablespoons fat in soup kettle.
Add chicken and ham. Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Add salt, pepper, onion, green peppers, thyme and tomatoes.
Add water.
Cover and allow to simmer 2 hours or until chicken is tender.
Add okra.
Cover and cook 20 minutes or until okra is tender.
If desired, remove chicken from bones.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream together sugar, butter, or shortening and eggs.
Add pumpkin and juice.
In another bowl sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt, all spice and cinnamon together.
Add to first mixture.
Mix until blended.
Add nuts and dates.
Place in two greased loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven about 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until bread springs back to touch.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix corned beef, cheese, onions and cooked macaroni in casserole dish.
Mix together the milk and soup with wire whisk until smooth.
Pour soup mixture over corned beef mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm.

title: marshmallow salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water with marshmallows, then add pineapple, cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Let chill.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Trim off leaves of broccoli.
Remove tough ends of stalks. Wash and chop coarsely.
Add onions, eggs and carrots to broccoli and toss.
Mix remaining ingredients in a small bowl.
Pour over broccoli mixture and toss gently.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Makes 12 servings.
Will keep 3 or 4 days in refrigerator.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Add oil and eggs.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar.
Add to sugar mixture. Add vanilla and mix well.
Chill.
Form into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press flat with bottom of glass which has been dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Yields 6 dozen.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer graham crackers, coconut, butterscotch chips, chocolate chips, Eagle Brand milk and nuts. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In large bowl, beat with electric mixer creamed cheese, peanut butter, sugar and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Gently fold in whipped topping.
Pour into baked pie shell and freeze for 4 to 6 hours.
Thaw 10 minutes before serving.

title: popsicles
directions: Gather, wash and cut up squash into small pieces.
Put in a large pot, cover with water and bring to a boil.
Wash pint or quart jars.
Fill with boiled squash.
Finish filling with the water in pot.
Cover with lids and pressure cook pints 25 minutes at 10 pounds pressure or quarts for 30 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.

title: bubble pizza
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Cut the biscuits in quarters and mix with the ground beef and sauce.
Put into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove and top with cheese.
Return to oven and bake 10 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Spread apples in 8 inch pan.
Sprinkle with mixture of water, cinnamon and salt.
Work together sugar, flour and butter until crumbly; spread over apples.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Pour all ingredients in a dish. Brown pork chops and place on top of rice. Bake at 400° for 1 hour covered. Uncover after 30 minutes. Bake until all the soup is gone.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Combine butter, egg and coconut flavoring.
Add Bisquick and Potato Buds a little at a time.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Do not use lower rack!!!

title: tacos
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Add taco seasoning and cook for 20 minutes.
Put in shell; add fixins.
Put some spicy salsa on top.

title: orange candied yams
directions: Boil the water, sugar and chopped oranges 5 minutes.
Add all remaining ingredients except cornstarch and water (4 teaspoons water).
Cook until butter is melted.
Dissolve cornstarch in water.
Add to sauce.
Boil until thick and syrupy about 20 minutes.

title: recipe for happiness
directions: "Cook popcorn in pot for 2 hours.
Put peanut butter in it. Spread it over it.
Put cheese on top and eat it."

title: quick and easy hot cheese dip
directions: Combine in a 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Microwave on High 3 minutes. Stir, then microwave 2 minutes more.

title: oyster stew
directions: Saute the oysters in the butter in a 3 or 4 quart saucepan (preferably stainless steel or porcelain) until the edges curl (or ruffle).
Add the milk and canned milk.
Get hot but don't boil (about to curdle), season with salt and pepper before serving. Serves 6.

title: ann's mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except the cheese.
Pour half of the batter into a greased baking pan.
Arrange cheese slices on top of batter.
Cover with the remaining batter.
Bake in a preheated 350 degree oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add buttermilk and oil.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to liquid measurements.
Stir.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt margarine.
Add cocoa with beaten eggs, flour and milk. Add salt and sugar.
Beat well, then add nuts and beat more.
Pour in greased pan 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°. Pour marshmallows over cake while still hot.
Put cake in warm oven until marshmallows melt.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 10 minutes at 350°, then 30 minutes at 325°.

title: stuffed eggs
directions: Boil eggs 10 minutes.
Peel and slice in half lengthwise.
Put yellows in small bowl.
Place whites on serving dish.
With mashed yellows, add a little sweet pickle relish, chopped onion, salt, pepper and enough salad dressing to hold together.
Mix real good. Take egg whites and fill with yolk mixture.
Sprinkle a little paprika on top of each white for color.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and 3 tbsp sugar. Put in a 13x10 in dish.
Bake at 400 for 8 minutes.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Sprinkle chuck with salt.
Place in deep bowl.	Combine other ingredients in saucepan, boil; pour over meat.
Place in refrigerator to marinate for 3 or
days,
turning meat over every day.	When ready to cook,
remove
meat,
dry with paper towel, strain and reserve marinade.
Dredge
meat
with
flour and brown in hot fat in heavy pan.
Add 1 cup marinade to meat and cover.
Cook about 3 hours, slowly in 350° oven.
Add more liquid if needed.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Prepare gelatin by package directions.
Prepare Jell-O; be sure to let water boil.
Remove orange peel.
In food processor, process oranges and cranberries.

title: two minute cookie
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a boil. Boil 2 minutes only, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add all other ingredients.
Drop by spoonful onto wax paper.

title: sweet onion bake
directions: Saute onions in butter until limp.
Cook rice in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Mix rice with onions.
Add cheese and milk.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake covered 1 hour at 300°.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Salt chicken, spread sour cream on both sides.
Put cheese crackers in blender until they are crumbs.
Roll chicken in cheese crumbs.
Melt butter in baking dish and place chicken in it.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown meat, onions,
taco
seasoning
and garlic powder together.
In separate saucepan warm soups, tomato sauce, milk and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
In
a
large casserole dish, layer chips which have been slightly	crushed,
meat, soup mix and cheese. Repeat, ending with cheese.
Bake
at
for
hour or until thoroughly heated through.	Serves 12.

title: neiman chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Cream butter and both sugars. Add eggs and vanilla. Combine flour, blended oatmeal (made by processing oatmeal to a fine powder, 2 cups at a time, in a blender), salt, baking powder and soda. Add chocolate, grated candy bar and nuts. Roll into balls and place 2-inches apart on a cookie sheet. Bake for 6 minutes. Makes about 112 cookies.

title: indian pumpkin bread(two 9 x 5-inch loaves)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large mixing bowl, blend sugars and oil.
Add egg and beat until light and fluffy.
Blend in pumpkin. Combine dry ingredients and blend into pumpkin mixture.
Stir in raisins and walnuts.

title: hot holiday punch
directions: Mix the ingredients and heat over medium heat until boiling slightly.
Serve hot.
Serves 25 punch cup servings.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter in cooking pan.
Heat until boiling.
Pour over eggs, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla. Cover bottom of pie shell with pecans, then pour mixture over nuts.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: baked chicken and dressing
directions: Cook chicken breasts in microwave.
Cut into thin strips. Place in 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Mix the cream of chicken soup with 1 soup can of milk.
Pour over chicken strips.
Prepare stuffing according to package directions.
Spoon over chicken/soup.
Bake at 350° until hot through and bubbly, 15 to 25 minutes.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Warm corn, sweet pepper and butter in saucepan while coring tomatoes.
Heat oven to 350°.
Put tomatoes in baking dish and fill with corn mixture (drained).
Heat in oven long enough to heat tomatoes, about 8 or 9 minutes.
Serve.

title: green salad
directions: Combine all the ingredients except the egg whites.
Blend well (don't beat). Add more milk, if mixture seems too stiff.
Be careful, don't add too much.
Fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Pour cooked green beans in casserole.
Make a layer of water chestnuts.
Empty can of mushroom soup on top of water chestnuts. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Take out and cover with onion rings.
Put back in oven for 5 minutes.

title: sweet spareribs with garlic
directions: Place ribs in a large roaster; cover with water and bring to a boil over high heat.
Lower the heat, skim the foam, cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Transfer ribs to paper towels to drain. Discard the water.
Preheat the oven to 300°.

title: eggs newport(great for brunch)
directions: Blend soup, mayonnaise and half and half together until smooth. Drizzle soup mixture on the bottom of a 9 x 13 Pyrex baking dish. Place a layer of sliced eggs in dish. Cover with soup mixture; repeat layering. Top with sauce. Sprinkle the chopped cooked bacon around edges of dish. Bake for 20 minutes in 325° oven.

title: holiday morning french toast
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter and 1 teaspoon cinnamon in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add apples and cranberries; toss to coat well. Spread apple mixture evenly over bottom of baking dish. Arrange slices of bread on top.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mix well.
For each serving, put 2 teaspoons or more into cup.
Pour hot water and stir.

title: penuchi nuts
directions: Cook sugar and milk until a soft ball forms when dropped in ice water.
Remove from fire.
Stir until it becomes creamy.
Add vanilla, butter and pecans.
Continue stirring until nuts separate and are covered with sugar coating.

title: fish cakes
directions: Mix together stuffing mix, water, mayonnaise, fish, lemon juice, cheese, and vegetables. Cover and refrigerate for 10 minutes. Heat nonstick skillet sprayed with cooking spray on medium heat. Shape 1/3 cupfuls of the stuffing mixture into pattie, add to skillet, cook 3 minutes on each side or until golden brown on both sides.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat sugars, butter, vanilla, milk and eggs until fluffy.
Mix flour with soda and salt; blend into butter mixture.
Stir in chips.
Drop batter onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop into hot oil by spoonfuls. Done when golden brown.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Reserve 1 cup flour to roll fruit in. Cream sugar and shortening. Add eggs and 1 1/2 cups flour to mixture, then add vanilla.
Put remaining cup of flour on chopped fruit and nuts, stirring gently. Add to rest of mixture.
Make into 4 or more rolls. Chill. Slice and bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: moist banana bundt cake
directions: In blender, blend bananas, hot water and soda until thick. In a bowl, beat eggs, oleo and vanilla on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add flour and banana mixture.
Add nuts a little at a time.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Bake 70 minutes at 350°.

title: polish lasagna
directions: Saute cabbage; prepare mashed potatoes and boil noodles.
Melt margarine
and saute onions.
Layer in 13 x 9-inch pan as follows: noodles, potatoes, cheese, cabbage, noodles, etc.
Put butter and onions between layers and on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: salsa chicken
directions: Use a little oil or Pam to spray frypan.
Brown chicken on both sides.
Add salsa; cook on low for 20 to 30 minutes.
Add sour cream; cook for 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Serve over angel hair pasta.
Serves 3 to 5 persons.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix together and bake at 325° for 1 hour or more.

title: tommy's homemade deer jerky
directions: Deer ham slices best when thawed only until ice frozen in middle of meat.
Mix all marinade ingredients together in a bowl separate from meat.
Add more of less of any ingredients to your taste.
Add cayenne lightly.
Pour over sliced deer and marinate in refrigerator for 12 hours.
